1
00:00:52,904 --> 00:00:57,604
In 1833, nothing was faster
than horse hooves.

2
00:00:58,069 --> 00:01:01,903
Passengers and letters depended
of horses and men.

3
00:01:02,321 --> 00:01:07,573
And the news wasn't faster
than a fast horse.

4
00:01:07,820 --> 00:01:09,948
But then, like today,

5
00:01:09,988 --> 00:01:14,165
the journalists
they searched without ceasing

6
00:01:14,164 --> 00:01:17,768
the fastest ways
to broadcast the news.

7
00:01:17,882 --> 00:01:22,080
"Swift and truth" was
the axiom of the profession.

8
00:01:22,131 --> 00:01:26,252
Julius Reuter, dedicated his life
to this axiom.

9
00:01:26,381 --> 00:01:32,401
Today the great men of
journalism,

10
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:36,640
still live for these 2 words:
truth and speed.

11
00:01:36,757 --> 00:01:40,511
It's them, the men
of the fourth power,

12
00:01:40,645 --> 00:01:45,153
what this film is dedicated to.

13
00:01:54,621 --> 00:01:56,152
Here it comes!

14
00:02:10,542 --> 00:02:12,524
- Can I help you?
- No, thank you.

15
00:02:12,732 --> 00:02:13,996
Can I help you?

16
00:02:14,028 --> 00:02:16,228
No, no, no!
Okay!

17
00:02:16,784 --> 00:02:18,557
Welcome, sir.

18
00:02:19,183 --> 00:02:21,859
Could you tell me where it is?
the Bender bank?

19
00:02:22,067 --> 00:02:23,111
- The Bender bank?
- Yes.

20
00:02:24,154 --> 00:02:26,031
Do you see the boy
with the hat?

21
00:02:26,031 --> 00:02:26,622
Yes.

22
00:02:26,622 --> 00:02:27,943
He works there.

23
00:02:28,117 --> 00:02:28,673
Thanks.

24
00:02:28,673 --> 00:02:30,689
I've waited long enough!

25
00:02:30,827 --> 00:02:33,610
Can I have my mail now?

26
00:02:33,610 --> 00:02:35,314
- You'll have to wait.
- Boy.

27
00:02:35,765 --> 00:02:37,224
My name is Julius Reuter.

28
00:02:37,677 --> 00:02:41,500
Sorry, Mr. Reuter. Could you
take me to the Bender bank?

29
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:44,143
- As soon as you have my mail.
- Thanks.

30
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:47,437
Uncle! Uncle!

31
00:02:48,438 --> 00:02:52,811
The London and Paris mail
is delayed because of the storms.

32
00:02:52,963 --> 00:02:55,775
When it's not the rain,
It's the drought!

33
00:02:55,892 --> 00:02:58,429
There's always an excuse...

34
00:02:58,429 --> 00:03:01,071
to the inefficiency of
our courier service!

35
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:03,087
But, wait!

36
00:03:04,269 --> 00:03:05,764
- It's uncle!
- Silence!

37
00:03:06,669 --> 00:03:08,340
That knight wants to see you.

38
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:10,809
Pardon me.

39
00:03:11,037 --> 00:03:13,089
- It's okay.
- What do you want?

40
00:03:13,332 --> 00:03:15,626
- I want to raise money.
- How much?

41
00:03:15,626 --> 00:03:16,706
100 florins.

42
00:03:16,706 --> 00:03:18,824
Do you have a letter of credit?

43
00:03:19,154 --> 00:03:19,883
Yes.

44
00:03:20,499 --> 00:03:24,290
I am Carew, earthly messenger
from India to England.

45
00:03:24,534 --> 00:03:27,313
From India over land?

46
00:03:27,557 --> 00:03:30,005
It's faster than by sea.

47
00:03:30,268 --> 00:03:34,023
When I arrive in London I bring news
from India at just 1 month old.

48
00:03:34,023 --> 00:03:36,576
When I'm luckier than this time...

49
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,600
But I will make up the time
when you arrive in Cologne.

50
00:03:38,751 --> 00:03:41,218
Cologne?
It's shorter for Hamburg!

51
00:03:41,218 --> 00:03:43,931
A special train
take me to Ostend,

52
00:03:43,931 --> 00:03:46,607
and there, I will cross the English Channel.

53
00:03:46,815 --> 00:03:49,875
Like a special train?
That must cost a fortune!

54
00:03:49,875 --> 00:03:51,821
Julius! Don't be insolent!

55
00:03:51,821 --> 00:03:53,456
It's okay.

56
00:03:53,456 --> 00:03:55,437
Look, boy.

57
00:03:55,437 --> 00:03:57,349
I mean, Mr. Reuters...

58
00:03:57,349 --> 00:04:00,061
that the Times
It is the richest newspaper.

59
00:04:00,061 --> 00:04:02,599
Money is not a problem.

60
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:05,605
The news is the thing
most important in the world!

61
00:04:05,605 --> 00:04:07,414
Even at 1 month old?

62
00:04:07,414 --> 00:04:10,575
Yes, because you can't have
earlier!

63
00:04:11,785 --> 00:04:13,870
Very soon it will be faster!

64
00:04:13,870 --> 00:04:16,860
There is a teacher who
calls Gauss.

65
00:04:17,446 --> 00:04:20,957
Sends signals via cable
to your friend Weber.

66
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:24,433
He says they communicate
It's the speed of light.

67
00:04:24,433 --> 00:04:26,615
- Cable!
- If it works.

68
00:04:26,772 --> 00:04:27,733
It will work!

69
00:04:27,758 --> 00:04:28,680
Julius!

70
00:04:29,089 --> 00:04:31,486
Focus on your
work!

71
00:04:31,540 --> 00:04:33,703
But Professor Gauss says...

72
00:04:33,728 --> 00:04:35,790
But can he do what he says?

73
00:04:35,815 --> 00:04:37,033
I am sure!

74
00:04:37,307 --> 00:04:38,946
I need to see it to believe it.

75
00:04:39,021 --> 00:04:42,115
Judge for yourself.

76
00:04:43,251 --> 00:04:44,678
Professor Gauss!

77
00:04:44,678 --> 00:04:47,354
You must not disturb the teacher!

78
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,718
- He's working.
- We come?

79
00:04:49,718 --> 00:04:50,864
Not now.

80
00:04:51,108 --> 00:04:53,159
There he is, with his telescope.

81
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,504
- What's the matter?
- Hans!

82
00:04:57,905 --> 00:04:59,644
What does the teacher do?

83
00:05:00,445 --> 00:05:03,016
Look at the receiver...

84
00:05:03,016 --> 00:05:07,015
because your friend Weber
try to send

85
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:08,960
cable signals.

86
00:05:09,494 --> 00:05:11,755
If the signals reach here,

87
00:05:12,207 --> 00:05:15,544
will make you vibrate
the magnetic coil

88
00:05:15,712 --> 00:05:18,722
and the teacher will decode the message.

89
00:05:18,887 --> 00:05:20,103
It works!

90
00:05:20,103 --> 00:05:22,642
The signal arrived perfectly.

91
00:05:22,642 --> 00:05:23,928
It works!

92
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:25,527
I knew!

93
00:05:25,527 --> 00:05:28,098
You must write it in
your newspaper!

94
00:05:28,098 --> 00:05:29,976
What should I say?

95
00:05:29,976 --> 00:05:33,280
"Prof. Gauss invented a way
to send signals.”

96
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:36,044
When the world knows,
will use this invention.

97
00:05:36,177 --> 00:05:38,563
And the threads will multiply!

98
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:25,878
I did a lot of good coming here.

99
00:06:25,878 --> 00:06:27,510
- What is this?
- Anything.

100
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:31,718
"Reuter's pigeons
deliver messages faster

101
00:06:31,718 --> 00:06:36,064
than those sent by
stagecoach or messenger."

102
00:06:36,551 --> 00:06:38,914
- It's fascinating!
- Indeed.

103
00:06:38,914 --> 00:06:42,286
I'm talking about pigeons!
Is it something new?

104
00:06:42,511 --> 00:06:43,765
Tell me more!

105
00:06:43,765 --> 00:06:47,971
Let's forget about work.
There is something...

106
00:06:50,474 --> 00:06:52,176
Hang on! What's your name?

107
00:06:52,176 --> 00:06:52,976
Max!

108
00:06:53,740 --> 00:06:55,028
Good morning, Julius!

109
00:06:55,028 --> 00:06:57,148
I entrusted you with a job!

110
00:06:57,148 --> 00:06:59,477
I was going to put up a poster.

111
00:06:59,477 --> 00:07:01,529
And why not here?

112
00:07:01,529 --> 00:07:04,309
People should know
our service.

113
00:07:04,309 --> 00:07:05,561
Didn't I put it here?

114
00:07:05,561 --> 00:07:08,411
No, not even in front of the Chamber
nor at the station.

115
00:07:08,411 --> 00:07:10,186
- Not even in hostels?
- No.

116
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:16,234
Why make things more difficult?

117
00:07:16,234 --> 00:07:17,833
I can't count on you?

118
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:18,736
Julius...

119
00:07:18,944 --> 00:07:21,899
Pigeons don't fascinate me as much
like you.

120
00:07:22,451 --> 00:07:26,552
If you help me, you can see them
fly with a paid message.

121
00:07:26,691 --> 00:07:28,917
This would allow us to eat.

122
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:30,654
This makes me hungry!

123
00:07:30,654 --> 00:07:32,288
Is it useless?

124
00:07:35,104 --> 00:07:37,155
Go back to the office!

125
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,423
You do it very well, Julius!

126
00:07:40,701 --> 00:07:42,196
Go back to the office!

127
00:07:48,662 --> 00:07:50,862
Send a telegram
to Arnheim.

128
00:07:50,909 --> 00:07:53,309
There is no telegraph line.

129
00:07:53,309 --> 00:07:55,080
Pass through another city.

130
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:58,558
There is no other line between
Belgium and Germany.

131
00:07:58,558 --> 00:08:00,713
It's a question of
life or death.

132
00:08:00,713 --> 00:08:03,563
An employee put
a wrong label.

133
00:08:03,563 --> 00:08:06,727
I sent the poison to Mrs. Magnus,

134
00:08:06,727 --> 00:08:09,056
and she has already left for Arnheim!

135
00:08:09,056 --> 00:08:10,864
The diligence must stop.

136
00:08:10,864 --> 00:08:13,122
Just one thing to do.

137
00:08:13,122 --> 00:08:14,653
Send a messenger!

138
00:08:16,044 --> 00:08:17,122
Quickly!

139
00:08:17,122 --> 00:08:18,999
Hurry, please!

140
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:28,107
It will never arrive in time.

141
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:31,131
- Never!
- But if the horse is fast!

142
00:08:31,374 --> 00:08:34,364
Impossible, due diligence
It takes 6 hours in advance.

143
00:08:34,816 --> 00:08:36,797
When you arrive in Bremen,

144
00:08:37,426 --> 00:08:39,919
these people will be poisoned!

145
00:08:41,209 --> 00:08:42,604
Did Arnheim say?

146
00:08:43,508 --> 00:08:45,386
Come, I can help you.

147
00:09:01,723 --> 00:09:03,324
Who is it aimed at?

148
00:09:03,533 --> 00:09:06,139
Dr. Magnus,
Arnheim hospital.

149
00:09:06,139 --> 00:09:07,564
The message,
please!

150
00:09:07,564 --> 00:09:09,823
"Dear doctor,
I have to..."

151
00:09:09,823 --> 00:09:11,840
No.
This is not a letter!

152
00:09:14,065 --> 00:09:16,986
"Fever medicine
poisoned.

153
00:09:17,104 --> 00:09:19,280
Do not use."

154
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:21,121
Sign, please.

155
00:09:21,121 --> 00:09:24,007
Is it really 200 km from here?

156
00:09:24,007 --> 00:09:26,789
Yes, by the road.
But don't look at it like a bird.

157
00:09:26,789 --> 00:09:28,005
Max! Max!

158
00:09:48,134 --> 00:09:49,454
This is it...

159
00:09:49,454 --> 00:09:50,255
Why two?

160
00:09:50,457 --> 00:09:52,056
Three will be sent.

161
00:09:52,193 --> 00:09:54,348
To be sure
that a pigeon will arrive.

162
00:09:55,122 --> 00:09:57,520
Risks must be avoided.

163
00:09:57,728 --> 00:09:58,737
- And this one!

164
00:09:58,737 --> 00:10:00,406
Max, where are you?

165
00:10:05,273 --> 00:10:07,600
Max. Why not
to respond?

166
00:10:21,890 --> 00:10:23,210
What happened?

167
00:10:24,426 --> 00:10:26,340
You called, didn't you?

168
00:10:26,583 --> 00:10:29,537
I stumbled
and the door...

169
00:10:29,781 --> 00:10:31,971
They all flew...

170
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:34,334
Was it all?

171
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:44,278
Lenchen, my friend,
don't disappoint me.

172
00:10:44,487 --> 00:10:46,745
Human lives are at stake.

173
00:10:46,745 --> 00:10:50,083
Lenchen,
Can I count on you.

174
00:10:50,208 --> 00:10:51,841
You understand!

175
00:10:52,134 --> 00:10:53,872
You can become a hero,

176
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:56,479
or a heroine...

177
00:10:56,896 --> 00:10:58,704
Do you trust me, Lenchen?

178
00:10:58,704 --> 00:11:00,374
Of course, isn't it?

179
00:11:03,890 --> 00:11:04,725
There it is.

180
00:11:04,928 --> 00:11:07,986
Fly as fast as possible.

181
00:11:08,091 --> 00:11:09,689
Why so much fuss?

182
00:11:09,689 --> 00:11:11,707
A message, Max!
Finally!

183
00:11:11,707 --> 00:11:13,514
Our future flies with Lenchen.

184
00:12:02,878 --> 00:12:04,304
Arnheim.

185
00:12:06,493 --> 00:12:08,488
Your father wants you to go to
the hospital.

186
00:12:08,636 --> 00:12:10,758
Okay, Emma.
Take care of the bags.

187
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:15,821
- Hi, Geller!
- Hello Miss Magnus.

188
00:12:16,159 --> 00:12:17,653
Hurry, Heinrich!

189
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:20,227
You have to send them
to Brussels.

190
00:12:20,227 --> 00:12:23,563
These pigeons all arrived today.
Business must be good!

191
00:12:23,563 --> 00:12:25,927
I wish so,

192
00:12:25,927 --> 00:12:29,125
but they arrived together
and no message.

193
00:12:29,382 --> 00:12:31,534
It shouldn't...

194
00:12:32,101 --> 00:12:34,474
trust beginners.

195
00:12:34,499 --> 00:12:38,061
These idiots from Brussels,
they let us escape.

196
00:12:39,484 --> 00:12:41,570
There's another one.

197
00:12:43,206 --> 00:12:44,733
Lenchen!

198
00:12:45,603 --> 00:12:48,871
You too? Come here.

199
00:12:50,252 --> 00:12:53,426
What happened in Brussels?

200
00:12:53,426 --> 00:12:56,416
Why don't any of you
Do you have a message?

201
00:12:57,696 --> 00:12:59,711
You have one!

202
00:12:59,821 --> 00:13:01,317
Give it to me.

203
00:13:06,428 --> 00:13:09,626
"Doctor Magnus,
Central Hospital.”

204
00:13:23,044 --> 00:13:25,199
- Do you have the medicine?
- Yes father.

205
00:13:25,199 --> 00:13:26,416
I hope this eases your mind.

206
00:13:26,903 --> 00:13:27,911
Can I help you?

207
00:13:27,911 --> 00:13:30,624
No, no.
Don't take useless risks.

208
00:13:31,041 --> 00:13:32,743
Fever is contagious.

209
00:13:37,088 --> 00:13:39,869
Send Lenchen with the others!

210
00:13:39,869 --> 00:13:42,477
I gotta go!

211
00:14:13,069 --> 00:14:14,322
Read this.

212
00:14:24,610 --> 00:14:26,802
It could have been horrible.

213
00:14:28,803 --> 00:14:31,807
But... How did it come to
message so fast?

214
00:14:31,807 --> 00:14:33,441
By Reuters.

215
00:14:33,650 --> 00:14:35,526
- Who?
- Julius Reuter.

216
00:14:35,735 --> 00:14:37,892
They call it
"The Pigeon Madman".

217
00:14:46,130 --> 00:14:47,278
Arnheim.

218
00:14:49,572 --> 00:14:52,352
Pigeon crazy!

219
00:14:55,864 --> 00:14:57,637
Hello, Adelaide!

220
00:14:58,158 --> 00:14:59,341
Hello, Geller!

221
00:15:00,071 --> 00:15:01,495
Nice to see you.

222
00:15:01,495 --> 00:15:03,072
Lenchen has arrived
with a message?

223
00:15:03,267 --> 00:15:04,484
Yes.

224
00:15:04,509 --> 00:15:06,011
Wonderful!!
It was what we needed.

225
00:15:06,589 --> 00:15:07,519
- See you soon.
- Where you go?

226
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:09,902
Business at last
they start to go.

227
00:15:09,927 --> 00:15:14,030
Reuters, come!
I have something to say.

228
00:15:19,702 --> 00:15:20,952
Be brief.

229
00:15:22,353 --> 00:15:23,637
He saw what happened,

230
00:15:23,637 --> 00:15:27,687
understands the advantage of
use my pigeons.

231
00:15:27,716 --> 00:15:28,480
Pigeons!

232
00:15:28,574 --> 00:15:30,870
We did tests...

233
00:15:30,904 --> 00:15:34,797
You said you would tell me
how to make a lot of money!

234
00:15:34,797 --> 00:15:35,631
It's true, but!

235
00:15:36,885 --> 00:15:40,919
It takes 10 hours to go
from Brussels to Arnheim.

236
00:15:41,319 --> 00:15:44,831
I guarantee that my pigeons
takes less than 2 hours.

237
00:15:44,831 --> 00:15:47,543
I'm a banker,
not a pigeon expert!

238
00:15:47,543 --> 00:15:50,044
Your projects do not
interest me.

239
00:15:50,322 --> 00:15:52,617
You haven't heard...

240
00:15:52,617 --> 00:15:56,649
No reasonable business can
depend on pigeons.

241
00:15:56,649 --> 00:15:59,362
They didn't tell you
of the medicine?

242
00:15:59,362 --> 00:16:01,480
I don't listen to more than my common sense.

243
00:16:01,759 --> 00:16:05,758
Don't bother me anymore and leave,
or I'll throw you out on the street!

244
00:16:15,703 --> 00:16:19,350
Don't you know what my pigeon did
faster than diligence!

245
00:16:19,385 --> 00:16:23,138
I don't want to hear any more
of your pigeons.

246
00:16:24,462 --> 00:16:25,817
Outside!

247
00:16:32,537 --> 00:16:34,194
Pigeons!

248
00:16:42,572 --> 00:16:44,728
Geller, he didn't know.

249
00:16:44,832 --> 00:16:46,675
The greatest banker!

250
00:16:47,093 --> 00:16:49,838
We could wait years for a
opportunity like this and kept it secret!

251
00:16:50,220 --> 00:16:52,933
I thought I had sense
to spread the story.

252
00:16:53,418 --> 00:16:56,999
Why didn't you disclose it?

253
00:16:57,242 --> 00:16:58,634
I couldn't.

254
00:16:58,634 --> 00:17:00,754
No?!
Why?

255
00:17:01,205 --> 00:17:03,396
I promise.

256
00:17:03,396 --> 00:17:06,004
Who asked you
this promise?

257
00:17:06,004 --> 00:17:09,029
I'd rather not say.

258
00:17:09,821 --> 00:17:12,360
It was the doctor!
He asked him to keep it secret.

259
00:17:13,895 --> 00:17:16,920
They make mistakes and
Should I pay for them?!

260
00:17:17,441 --> 00:17:19,874
Where are you going, Julius?

261
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:23,873
Father!
Mr. Reuter is here.

262
00:17:23,873 --> 00:17:25,644
Good. Come in.

263
00:17:28,496 --> 00:17:30,303
Come in, Mr. Reuters.

264
00:17:32,769 --> 00:17:36,732
Mr. Reuter, nice to see you!
Sit down.

265
00:17:41,914 --> 00:17:42,994
What happened?

266
00:17:43,142 --> 00:17:45,156
Did I offend you in something?

267
00:17:46,330 --> 00:17:47,686
Professor Magnus,

268
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:51,300
I don't like to talk bad
of others,

269
00:17:51,996 --> 00:17:54,603
but my life
It depends on my pigeons.

270
00:17:54,846 --> 00:17:57,386
People laugh at me,
but I didn't give up.

271
00:17:57,589 --> 00:18:01,035
Finally I would have been able to prove that
my pigeons were useful.

272
00:18:01,278 --> 00:18:03,989
But you denied me
this opportunity.

273
00:18:04,442 --> 00:18:06,145
I? As?

274
00:18:06,232 --> 00:18:07,744
- Don't you know?
- No.

275
00:18:08,482 --> 00:18:12,090
Mr. Reuter talks about something
of which I am responsible.

276
00:18:12,334 --> 00:18:13,515
- You?
- Yes.

277
00:18:13,932 --> 00:18:16,921
I asked Geller
to keep it secret.

278
00:18:17,565 --> 00:18:20,555
Sorry, I didn't know that
would harm him.

279
00:18:21,024 --> 00:18:23,110
That doesn't help me,
Miss Magnus.

280
00:18:23,110 --> 00:18:26,552
My business counts more to me
than your secrets.

281
00:18:27,177 --> 00:18:29,402
It's not an intimate secret.

282
00:18:30,201 --> 00:18:31,627
Try to understand.

283
00:18:32,079 --> 00:18:35,973
We save lives
but progress is slow.

284
00:18:35,973 --> 00:18:39,170
Some people still see us
like sorcerers,

285
00:18:39,435 --> 00:18:44,372
and prefer to cure themselves with
superstitions instead of science.

286
00:18:44,678 --> 00:18:46,278
What does it have to do with me?

287
00:18:47,077 --> 00:18:51,004
If this is known, all deaths from
fever will be attributed to poison,

288
00:18:51,004 --> 00:18:53,167
even the ones that happened
a long time ago.

289
00:18:53,403 --> 00:18:56,761
My father and his colleagues
they would pass for murderers.

290
00:18:56,899 --> 00:19:01,318
We couldn't go on
our investigations

291
00:19:01,376 --> 00:19:04,226
and the progress made
they would be lost.

292
00:19:05,015 --> 00:19:08,387
I'm sorry, but I think
that my daughter is right.

293
00:19:08,708 --> 00:19:10,968
Saving lives is more important
than business.

294
00:19:10,968 --> 00:19:15,105
But deciding to tell this story
There's nothing we can do.

295
00:19:17,121 --> 00:19:18,894
Don't worry.

296
00:19:20,042 --> 00:19:22,163
I'm not angry anymore.

297
00:19:23,134 --> 00:19:25,848
When I'm not angry
I can see other people's problems.

298
00:19:26,472 --> 00:19:27,967
Good days.

299
00:19:40,127 --> 00:19:42,699
It's not fair to Reuter,
Aren't you dad?

300
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,446
What can we do?

301
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:53,032
My Friend, I'm afraid...

302
00:19:53,032 --> 00:19:57,378
I owe you an apology
for your patience and help.

303
00:19:57,516 --> 00:20:00,610
Reuter, won't you think about giving up?

304
00:20:01,550 --> 00:20:02,871
To give up?

305
00:20:03,845 --> 00:20:05,616
It would be very difficult.

306
00:20:07,216 --> 00:20:09,372
But I know I lost.

307
00:20:09,858 --> 00:20:11,074
Lost!

308
00:20:12,117 --> 00:20:13,369
In between.

309
00:20:15,525 --> 00:20:17,402
O Miss Magnus!

310
00:20:17,888 --> 00:20:20,078
What a surprise!

311
00:20:20,774 --> 00:20:22,998
Most of all, in this weather.

312
00:20:23,207 --> 00:20:24,703
I like rain.

313
00:20:24,703 --> 00:20:26,336
But it rains a lot,

314
00:20:26,336 --> 00:20:29,325
and stopped here to dry.

315
00:20:29,569 --> 00:20:31,481
Sit down...

316
00:20:31,481 --> 00:20:33,393
near the fire.

317
00:20:34,297 --> 00:20:37,391
It's a good day to
sitting by the fire,

318
00:20:38,051 --> 00:20:39,511
isn't it?

319
00:20:41,076 --> 00:20:44,795
And it's time to
drink coffee.

320
00:20:50,949 --> 00:20:52,235
Pardon me.

321
00:20:52,478 --> 00:20:55,224
Stay, I'd like to talk
with you.

322
00:20:55,224 --> 00:20:56,546
I have a lot of work.

323
00:20:56,546 --> 00:20:59,084
Mr. Reuter, I came,

324
00:20:59,287 --> 00:21:02,659
because I'm worried
with your visit to my father.

325
00:21:04,021 --> 00:21:06,315
Maybe speaking...

326
00:21:06,416 --> 00:21:07,948
Let's find a solution.

327
00:21:08,073 --> 00:21:08,902
As?

328
00:21:09,152 --> 00:21:11,494
We could find a solution...

329
00:21:11,494 --> 00:21:13,824
that will help you.

330
00:21:14,241 --> 00:21:16,223
Help me find
my slippers.

331
00:21:16,223 --> 00:21:17,474
Slippers?

332
00:21:18,168 --> 00:21:19,873
I am really sorry.

333
00:21:23,697 --> 00:21:24,915
Thanks.

334
00:21:25,226 --> 00:21:26,235
Mr. Reuters.

335
00:21:27,138 --> 00:21:29,224
Don't hate us.

336
00:21:29,328 --> 00:21:30,824
Hate you?

337
00:21:31,204 --> 00:21:32,631
But why?

338
00:21:33,256 --> 00:21:34,994
They did well.

339
00:21:36,559 --> 00:21:39,793
I seem worried, because
I have things to think about.

340
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:42,311
I don't renounce my pigeons, and...

341
00:21:42,762 --> 00:21:44,360
As?

342
00:21:48,545 --> 00:21:50,214
- What is it?
- A pigeon.

343
00:21:50,284 --> 00:21:52,300
I must go and see.

344
00:21:52,723 --> 00:21:54,983
No, stay.
I go.

345
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:59,609
Will this carry a message?

346
00:21:59,725 --> 00:22:01,304
And if you bring it?

347
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:04,614
Mr. Reuter, can I go and see
the dovecote?

348
00:22:06,256 --> 00:22:08,655
Yes, if you want.

349
00:22:09,170 --> 00:22:10,316
Thanks.

350
00:22:15,032 --> 00:22:17,187
   Lenchen!

351
00:22:17,218 --> 00:22:18,888
That bird!

352
00:22:19,541 --> 00:22:21,593
He has the heart of a lion.

353
00:22:25,301 --> 00:22:27,427
So this is how they are sent
the messages?

354
00:22:27,517 --> 00:22:28,560
Yes.

355
00:22:28,811 --> 00:22:31,419
Come, Lenchen,
you must be hungry.

356
00:22:31,419 --> 00:22:34,687
Yes, in this little bag.

357
00:22:34,990 --> 00:22:37,421
It's very well folded,

358
00:22:37,446 --> 00:22:39,186
but see,

359
00:22:40,423 --> 00:22:41,847
opens up

360
00:22:43,551 --> 00:22:47,292
to get
a large piece of paper.

361
00:22:48,228 --> 00:22:49,620
See?

362
00:22:51,791 --> 00:22:53,460
Here is the message.

363
00:22:54,003 --> 00:22:56,714
More stock quotes!

364
00:22:57,945 --> 00:23:00,724
Look the other way.

365
00:23:00,724 --> 00:23:03,124
Certainly a word from Max.

366
00:23:03,124 --> 00:23:05,349
What counts, then?

367
00:23:05,443 --> 00:23:09,822
Russia's intervention
Hungary has just been confirmed.

368
00:23:10,111 --> 00:23:11,815
Russia intervenes to

369
00:23:11,815 --> 00:23:15,081
restore peace in Hungary and
maintain order in Poland.

370
00:23:15,534 --> 00:23:18,489
This can create difficulties
in Prussia!

371
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:20,795
If Poland revolts,

372
00:23:21,219 --> 00:23:24,904
That would be the crisis in Russia,
in England, in France.

373
00:23:26,085 --> 00:23:28,276
Is there a risk of provoking a war?

374
00:23:28,276 --> 00:23:31,301
We could get there,
but anyway,

375
00:23:31,544 --> 00:23:33,873
the stock market will sink tomorrow.

376
00:23:34,516 --> 00:23:37,575
It has just been confirmed.

377
00:23:39,158 --> 00:23:42,340
We won't know anything
in Arnheim until tomorrow.

378
00:23:42,703 --> 00:23:47,049
If the bankers listened to me,
would sell before tomorrow.

379
00:23:47,258 --> 00:23:48,699
But they won't do anything.

380
00:23:49,239 --> 00:23:51,289
You are safe
of this news?

381
00:23:51,289 --> 00:23:53,688
My agent never made a mistake.

382
00:23:54,765 --> 00:23:57,270
That might interest
to my father.

383
00:23:57,478 --> 00:23:59,738
- Goodbye, Mr. Reuter.
- Goodbye.

384
00:24:00,329 --> 00:24:02,344
Goodbye, Mrs. Magnus.

385
00:24:02,344 --> 00:24:03,562
Goodbye, Mr. Geller.

386
00:24:03,944 --> 00:24:05,369
Until the evening?

387
00:24:05,369 --> 00:24:07,247
Of course!

388
00:24:30,449 --> 00:24:32,176
How is it,
Professor Magnus?

389
00:24:32,316 --> 00:24:34,344
Mr Bauer, I was looking for him.

390
00:24:34,571 --> 00:24:37,282
Did you sell my shares like I asked?

391
00:24:37,282 --> 00:24:40,236
Yes, but I don't understand why.

392
00:24:40,236 --> 00:24:42,530
Russia will invade Hungary.

393
00:24:42,530 --> 00:24:45,731
Ah, these are rumors for
weaken the Stock Exchange!

394
00:24:45,731 --> 00:24:48,372
Absolutely.
It has been confirmed.

395
00:24:48,372 --> 00:24:50,214
- Where?
- In Brussels.

396
00:24:50,214 --> 00:24:52,718
In Brussels! Today!

397
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:55,395
And how did it arrive
the news?

398
00:24:55,603 --> 00:24:57,445
- By heaven.
- The sky?

399
00:24:57,445 --> 00:25:00,122
This is stupid!

400
00:25:00,331 --> 00:25:03,182
Rumors like that
can cost you dearly.

401
00:25:03,182 --> 00:25:06,798
The news arrived here
thanks to a pigeon.

402
00:25:06,798 --> 00:25:08,569
A Reuter's pigeon.

403
00:25:13,088 --> 00:25:15,349
Now I understand!

404
00:25:28,629 --> 00:25:31,026
What does this strange man do?
with Ida?

405
00:25:31,026 --> 00:25:32,419
Strange man?

406
00:25:32,696 --> 00:25:35,035
It's my friend, Julius Reuter.

407
00:25:35,102 --> 00:25:36,770
Why strange"?

408
00:25:36,833 --> 00:25:40,102
Because it doesn't have a look
prosperous...

409
00:25:40,310 --> 00:25:41,700
But after all!

410
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:44,690
Exactly! After all!

411
00:25:50,913 --> 00:25:52,581
I didn't behave very badly,
why not?

412
00:25:52,581 --> 00:25:55,431
It's okay.
You'll do better next time.

413
00:25:55,431 --> 00:25:56,578
I hope so.

414
00:25:58,794 --> 00:25:59,905
My daughter.

415
00:26:00,244 --> 00:26:03,635
Mr. Stein, Mr. Frank, Mr. Von Constad,

416
00:26:03,635 --> 00:26:05,722
and Mr. Bauer, here is Mr. Reuter.

417
00:26:05,722 --> 00:26:07,669
I already know Mr. Reuter.

418
00:26:07,669 --> 00:26:12,362
M. Reuter, wants to convince us
this nonsense

419
00:26:12,362 --> 00:26:16,885
brought by a pigeon
for some reason invented by you?

420
00:26:17,637 --> 00:26:18,992
Mr. Bauer,

421
00:26:19,141 --> 00:26:23,694
I can tolerate lack of respect
for my desire to innovate,

422
00:26:24,781 --> 00:26:27,835
but not for my integrity.

423
00:26:28,492 --> 00:26:31,608
I hope your apology
after reading the morning newspapers.

424
00:26:32,108 --> 00:26:35,238
French troops are
At the gates of Rome.

425
00:26:35,511 --> 00:26:39,304
Brussels confirms the
Russian intervention in Hungary.

426
00:26:39,826 --> 00:26:43,615
The Hungarians are at their limit
and ponder the uprising.

427
00:26:44,137 --> 00:26:46,326
The Grand Duke of Posen

428
00:26:46,326 --> 00:26:48,932
threatens to take sides
in this movement.

429
00:26:48,932 --> 00:26:52,270
Now, they will believe in you.
Those fools!

430
00:26:52,850 --> 00:26:53,626
Perhaps.

431
00:26:54,322 --> 00:26:55,956
I don't know.

432
00:26:56,895 --> 00:27:01,007
People take a while to see
what goes on in front of their noses.

433
00:27:01,926 --> 00:27:03,662
In between.

434
00:27:08,094 --> 00:27:10,696
Beautiful day after yesterday's storm!

435
00:27:11,086 --> 00:27:13,172
Yes, beautiful day!

436
00:27:13,963 --> 00:27:15,284
How about it, Geller?

437
00:27:15,284 --> 00:27:17,196
Very good, Mr. Bauer.

438
00:27:17,196 --> 00:27:19,005
Exceptionally well.

439
00:27:19,005 --> 00:27:20,085
Great.

440
00:27:21,062 --> 00:27:22,903
Pardon me.

441
00:27:27,269 --> 00:27:28,380
Yes?

442
00:27:29,156 --> 00:27:32,110
I know how to recognize my mistakes.

443
00:27:32,203 --> 00:27:34,962
You were right
and Dr. Magnus

444
00:27:34,962 --> 00:27:37,151
made a good profit.

445
00:27:38,243 --> 00:27:40,816
I'm afraid I misjudged him.

446
00:27:47,014 --> 00:27:51,022
After all, making mistakes is human.

447
00:27:52,575 --> 00:27:53,759
Yes?

448
00:27:54,497 --> 00:27:55,159
Good.

449
00:27:55,408 --> 00:27:58,710
Anyway, sorry.

450
00:27:59,922 --> 00:28:01,937
Now, let's talk business.

451
00:28:01,937 --> 00:28:06,240
It says that pigeons are
faster than a messenger.

452
00:28:06,329 --> 00:28:07,684
I guarantee.

453
00:28:07,810 --> 00:28:11,011
But your service
depends on the electric telegraph.

454
00:28:11,315 --> 00:28:14,800
Soon we will have agents
in every capital of Europe.

455
00:28:15,292 --> 00:28:19,008
They will telegraph the quotations
at the nearest terminal.

456
00:28:19,203 --> 00:28:22,309
Arnheim is the most
close to Eastern Europe.

457
00:28:22,309 --> 00:28:24,430
Brussels is the closest
to the West.

458
00:28:24,430 --> 00:28:27,350
My pigeons will gather
both terminals.

459
00:28:27,350 --> 00:28:29,481
But the telegraph
It's very expensive.

460
00:28:29,668 --> 00:28:33,208
Only the big banks have
the means to use it.

461
00:28:33,325 --> 00:28:35,965
That's what makes my idea original.

462
00:28:36,076 --> 00:28:38,788
A telegram
will be sent to each agent.

463
00:28:38,954 --> 00:28:41,869
The cost will be shared
between bankers and brokers,

464
00:28:41,894 --> 00:28:45,165
and thus it will be more economical.

465
00:28:46,749 --> 00:28:50,155
You have a practical spirit,
not like me.

466
00:28:50,322 --> 00:28:51,550
I accept.

467
00:28:51,714 --> 00:28:54,243
You will be the first to sign.

468
00:28:56,378 --> 00:28:57,769
Please.

469
00:28:58,027 --> 00:29:00,308
I will sign, but with one condition.

470
00:29:00,386 --> 00:29:01,246
Yes?

471
00:29:01,511 --> 00:29:04,757
I will pay for exclusive use of your service.

472
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:08,226
- Exclusive?
- Absolutely.

473
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:10,008
Impossible!

474
00:29:10,008 --> 00:29:11,433
Think about it, Reuters!

475
00:29:11,711 --> 00:29:14,980
With this advantage,
we will make a fortune.

476
00:29:17,482 --> 00:29:20,089
Thanks for coming,
Mr. Bauer.

477
00:29:20,089 --> 00:29:21,723
What's wrong with you?

478
00:29:21,801 --> 00:29:24,200
Your proposal doesn't help me
interest.

479
00:29:25,513 --> 00:29:27,532
is smarter than
I thought.

480
00:29:27,822 --> 00:29:30,533
Gave him part of my profits.

481
00:29:30,658 --> 00:29:31,388
No.

482
00:29:31,388 --> 00:29:32,673
What if we join together?

483
00:29:33,043 --> 00:29:33,738
Mr. Bauer,

484
00:29:34,413 --> 00:29:38,446
If I explore this idea,
I will have all the profits.

485
00:29:38,446 --> 00:29:39,870
Without sharing them with you.

486
00:29:39,870 --> 00:29:41,247
But I have other ideas.

487
00:29:41,272 --> 00:29:44,366
I want to build my future
at the service of others.

488
00:29:49,639 --> 00:29:51,447
And that too
could help you.

489
00:29:52,784 --> 00:29:54,836
- Hello Bauer.
- How are you, Constadt?

490
00:29:55,931 --> 00:29:58,120
Constadt, please.

491
00:29:58,748 --> 00:30:02,711
Mr. Reuter, may I have the honor of
Be your first user?

492
00:30:06,638 --> 00:30:08,654
Come, gentlemen.

493
00:30:09,002 --> 00:30:11,818
Mr. Reuter will receive it.

494
00:30:16,407 --> 00:30:17,660
Geller!

495
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:21,656
- How is Mr. Reuter here?
- Yes, Miss Magnus.

496
00:30:21,788 --> 00:30:23,395
Sorry,

497
00:30:23,395 --> 00:30:27,358
but only subscribers
can enter.

498
00:30:27,532 --> 00:30:28,643
Me neither?

499
00:30:28,643 --> 00:30:30,764
Mr. Reuters said

500
00:30:30,764 --> 00:30:34,623
no exceptions.
Business is business.

501
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:37,156
Knights,

502
00:30:37,156 --> 00:30:40,006
the first pigeon
You should arrive at 1:30 pm.

503
00:30:40,006 --> 00:30:43,761
Since your arrival,
the door will be locked.

504
00:30:44,062 --> 00:30:47,851
When you finish copying the numbers,
the door will be opened.

505
00:30:48,046 --> 00:30:49,295
Closed?

506
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:52,770
So that each one
be treated equally.

507
00:30:53,231 --> 00:30:56,778
If you think this is unfair,
he can go.

508
00:30:57,794 --> 00:31:00,019
Sit down, please.

509
00:31:00,019 --> 00:31:02,278
Only 15 minutes left to wait.

510
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:08,612
I still don't believe it.

511
00:31:08,612 --> 00:31:11,464
It's 13:15 and you
he promised us

512
00:31:11,464 --> 00:31:13,654
Paris, Brussels quotes
and London.

513
00:31:13,966 --> 00:31:16,122
Let's see if he fulfills his promise.

514
00:31:16,607 --> 00:31:17,999
It's here!

515
00:31:19,911 --> 00:31:21,718
Geller, open the door!

516
00:31:29,238 --> 00:31:30,976
Miss Magnus.

517
00:31:33,747 --> 00:31:37,015
I was prevented from entering,
so I came up here.

518
00:31:37,780 --> 00:31:39,449
Was it you who rang the doorbell?

519
00:31:40,178 --> 00:31:41,256
Yes.

520
00:31:41,604 --> 00:31:44,176
I knew you would come.

521
00:31:46,783 --> 00:31:48,952
I'm going to Brussels.

522
00:31:49,261 --> 00:31:52,945
I would like to see you
before leaving.

523
00:31:53,145 --> 00:31:54,397
Why?

524
00:31:55,579 --> 00:31:57,657
To wish you
good luck.

525
00:31:59,334 --> 00:32:01,349
Thank you Miss
Magnus.

526
00:32:01,802 --> 00:32:04,408
If I fail,
It won't be your fault.

527
00:32:04,652 --> 00:32:06,912
You forgive me this
false alarm?

528
00:32:06,912 --> 00:32:10,076
Of course,
but not the subscribers down there.

529
00:32:10,527 --> 00:32:13,065
- I'll warn them.
- Goodbye.

530
00:32:13,065 --> 00:32:13,865
No, no, please.

531
00:32:13,899 --> 00:32:15,012
You can't see it.

532
00:32:17,446 --> 00:32:19,983
I would prefer you to stay.

533
00:32:24,086 --> 00:32:26,137
I'll stay as long as I can.

534
00:32:30,412 --> 00:32:32,221
- Oh, gentlemen!
- So?

535
00:32:32,012 --> 00:32:34,097
It was a false alarm.

536
00:32:34,097 --> 00:32:35,940
He said they would arrive in minutes!

537
00:32:35,940 --> 00:32:38,234
I said at 1:30.

538
00:32:38,234 --> 00:32:39,659
It's already...

539
00:32:48,767 --> 00:32:51,549
Why don't they arrive?

540
00:32:51,549 --> 00:32:53,078
Come.

541
00:32:53,078 --> 00:32:55,894
What if Max let me down?

542
00:32:56,277 --> 00:32:58,989
- What was the scheduled time?
- 13:30.

543
00:32:58,989 --> 00:33:00,169
It's almost 2pm.

544
00:33:00,169 --> 00:33:02,291
Julius! Julius!

545
00:33:03,611 --> 00:33:04,968
What it was?

546
00:33:05,559 --> 00:33:07,921
- They're leaving!
- As?

547
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:14,423
- Oh, wait!

548
00:33:14,423 --> 00:33:17,413
- The pigeons will come.
- I've waited too long.

549
00:33:17,413 --> 00:33:20,194
A little patience!

550
00:33:20,194 --> 00:33:21,447
I've had a lot of patience.

551
00:33:21,447 --> 00:33:22,384
There they are!

552
00:33:32,743 --> 00:33:34,275
Close the door, Geller!

553
00:33:47,623 --> 00:33:50,440
3% loan 82.40 francs,

554
00:33:50,960 --> 00:33:53,568
5%, 117.40 francs.

555
00:33:55,723 --> 00:33:58,677
They will have London quotes
at 16:00.

556
00:33:58,990 --> 00:34:00,522
Did you write everything down?

557
00:34:00,522 --> 00:34:02,292
Open the door, Geller.

558
00:34:24,304 --> 00:34:25,626
Julius.

559
00:34:25,869 --> 00:34:29,034
For success
of your carrier pigeons!

560
00:34:30,354 --> 00:34:33,623
Must be the man
happier.

561
00:34:34,493 --> 00:34:37,551
Max. My best friend
and my worst enemy.

562
00:34:37,551 --> 00:34:39,393
But, Julius,

563
00:34:39,602 --> 00:34:42,001
Maybe it wasn't your fault.

564
00:34:42,001 --> 00:34:44,155
The quotes were incomplete.

565
00:34:44,155 --> 00:34:46,692
Nobody noticed.

566
00:34:46,867 --> 00:34:48,292
Except me!

567
00:34:48,796 --> 00:34:51,819
We need to be trustworthy.

568
00:34:52,412 --> 00:34:54,045
I don't know what to do.

569
00:34:59,096 --> 00:35:01,172
I must stay here,

570
00:35:02,076 --> 00:35:05,135
but also go to Brussels
to talk to Max.

571
00:35:06,873 --> 00:35:08,715
I could do it!

572
00:35:08,715 --> 00:35:09,793
You?

573
00:35:10,454 --> 00:35:11,602
Yes.

574
00:35:14,626 --> 00:35:16,364
I didn't want to bother her.

575
00:35:16,364 --> 00:35:18,243
But I'm going to Brussels!

576
00:35:18,972 --> 00:35:21,370
I must write a letter.

577
00:35:21,613 --> 00:35:24,741
Death threats
and destruction.

578
00:35:24,741 --> 00:35:27,731
On the contrary, I will tell you
that breaks my heart.

579
00:35:28,358 --> 00:35:31,451
Poor Max, we have to treat him
like a child!

580
00:35:33,843 --> 00:35:35,579
Write the letter,

581
00:35:35,579 --> 00:35:37,841
and deliver it to me before my departure.

582
00:35:44,258 --> 00:35:45,962
Almost forget!

583
00:35:46,363 --> 00:35:48,659
I did something for you.

584
00:35:49,112 --> 00:35:50,259
For me?

585
00:35:50,293 --> 00:35:51,370
Yes.

586
00:35:51,786 --> 00:35:53,317
A little bag.

587
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:55,891
For your pigeons to carry messages.

588
00:35:58,184 --> 00:36:00,688
But, I don't deserve it...

589
00:36:01,356 --> 00:36:03,304
Now, finish the letter...

590
00:36:04,719 --> 00:36:07,442
before leaving the stagecoach.

591
00:36:07,553 --> 00:36:09,291
Bon voyage!

592
00:36:09,380 --> 00:36:10,355
Thank you, Mr. Geller.

593
00:36:32,646 --> 00:36:34,384
I must say...

594
00:36:34,409 --> 00:36:37,537
I don't know what she sees in you.

595
00:36:37,537 --> 00:36:39,311
What murmurs?

596
00:36:40,007 --> 00:36:43,231
She likes you.

597
00:36:43,559 --> 00:36:45,325
You're crazy.

598
00:36:45,904 --> 00:36:47,223
For God,

599
00:36:47,698 --> 00:36:50,132
What could that beautiful girl do?
to see in me?

600
00:36:50,132 --> 00:36:53,574
- Exactly.
- Clear.

601
00:36:54,130 --> 00:36:55,520
What?

602
00:37:03,621 --> 00:37:04,941
Nonsense!

603
00:37:07,818 --> 00:37:11,643
Gave me one
explosive message.

604
00:37:12,281 --> 00:37:16,002
"Even a saint
I would lose patience with you."

605
00:37:16,414 --> 00:37:18,431
What violence, huh?

606
00:37:18,935 --> 00:37:20,659
I thought you were friends with Mr. Reuter.

607
00:37:20,715 --> 00:37:22,282
Since always!

608
00:37:22,897 --> 00:37:24,602
You should be ashamed.

609
00:37:24,602 --> 00:37:25,887
I suppose I should.

610
00:37:26,617 --> 00:37:28,982
You should pay attention to these signs!

611
00:37:28,982 --> 00:37:30,615
They're good, aren't they?

612
00:37:30,615 --> 00:37:31,936
Excellent.

613
00:37:31,936 --> 00:37:34,405
Mr Reuter did not put them
there to ignore them.

614
00:37:34,857 --> 00:37:37,359
No, I made them.

615
00:37:38,436 --> 00:37:40,871
Look:
"Reuter, the king of speed."

616
00:37:41,114 --> 00:37:43,999
If you have written this,
be up to par.

617
00:37:43,999 --> 00:37:47,545
Does an engineer have to sleep
in the tunnel he built?

618
00:37:48,137 --> 00:37:50,292
It's not funny.

619
00:37:50,292 --> 00:37:54,184
Sorry. Making slogans
I forgot about business.

620
00:37:57,384 --> 00:37:59,503
- Give me a broom.
- What are you going to do?

621
00:37:59,503 --> 00:38:02,111
I'm going to clean this trash can.

622
00:38:02,776 --> 00:38:04,614
Where can I find a broom?

623
00:38:04,718 --> 00:38:06,388
Find one!

624
00:38:08,056 --> 00:38:10,350
Don't throw away my poems!

625
00:38:10,835 --> 00:38:13,408
These are not poems.

626
00:38:13,656 --> 00:38:16,028
No, this is a message
to Reuters.

627
00:38:16,571 --> 00:38:18,483
Poor Julius Reuter!

628
00:38:18,761 --> 00:38:21,889
What time do pigeons come out?
To arrive on time.

629
00:38:22,546 --> 00:38:24,667
- About...
- Be precise.

630
00:38:24,855 --> 00:38:26,905
When exactly?

631
00:38:29,384 --> 00:38:31,052
There it is!

632
00:38:39,367 --> 00:38:41,208
Close the door.

633
00:38:56,465 --> 00:38:59,475
It's catching wind,
Mr. Bauer.

634
00:39:01,452 --> 00:39:03,191
Do I close the window?

635
00:39:03,191 --> 00:39:06,111
No thanks, I prefer some
of fresh air.

636
00:39:09,315 --> 00:39:11,721
Well, as you wish.

637
00:39:16,517 --> 00:39:19,766
Max is perfect.

638
00:39:19,891 --> 00:39:22,532
I did well to write the letter.

639
00:39:22,970 --> 00:39:23,774
What happened?

640
00:39:23,853 --> 00:39:26,495
Bauer's employee
It's here too.

641
00:39:26,719 --> 00:39:28,735
What are you going to do?

642
00:39:30,179 --> 00:39:32,333
Teach Bauer a lesson.

643
00:39:36,271 --> 00:39:39,751
Gentlemen, let's start with London.

644
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:44,997
These quotes are flying high, my friends
pigeons will lose sight of them!

645
00:39:44,997 --> 00:39:48,056
Stop the jokes!
Give us the numbers.

646
00:39:49,230 --> 00:39:51,246
Consols: 78.5.

647
00:39:51,324 --> 00:39:54,835
Funding Loan: 113 et 4.91%.

648
00:39:54,835 --> 00:39:56,261
Great Western Railway:

649
00:39:56,261 --> 00:39:57,790
2.56.

650
00:39:58,101 --> 00:40:00,049
Liverpool and Birkenhear: 9.05.

651
00:40:00,328 --> 00:40:02,067
That's all London.

652
00:40:18,337 --> 00:40:21,534
Attention,
I made a mistake.

653
00:40:21,742 --> 00:40:24,037
I'll say the numbers again.

654
00:40:24,037 --> 00:40:26,088
Great Western: 2.47.

655
00:40:26,505 --> 00:40:28,696
And Liverpool Birkenhead: 89.

656
00:40:29,113 --> 00:40:32,033
What a fall! More than 3 points.

657
00:40:37,559 --> 00:40:39,472
Stein, write down the numbers for me.

658
00:40:39,472 --> 00:40:42,253
- Open it.
- No, I'm sorry.

659
00:40:42,253 --> 00:40:43,714
I must leave immediately.

660
00:40:44,285 --> 00:40:47,203
No, no, you can't.

661
00:40:47,774 --> 00:40:51,199
Mr. Reuters.
Tell him to let me out!

662
00:40:51,379 --> 00:40:54,369
Of course, if gentlemen
are in agreement.

663
00:40:59,263 --> 00:41:01,028
Here are the numbers for Paris.

664
00:41:01,192 --> 00:41:04,112
Charleroi mining company:
169.75 francs.

665
00:41:04,199 --> 00:41:06,945
Shares of St. Tienne:
278 francs.

666
00:41:06,945 --> 00:41:11,046
Orleans Railway Company:
11.84; 3% slope...

667
00:41:13,342 --> 00:41:15,914
To the bank!
Quickly! Quickly!

668
00:41:23,528 --> 00:41:26,168
Did you see his face?

669
00:41:26,412 --> 00:41:29,332
This will teach you
not to overtake others.

670
00:41:33,052 --> 00:41:34,652
Professor Magnus!

671
00:41:34,652 --> 00:41:35,660
Are you okay?

672
00:41:35,660 --> 00:41:38,511
- Did you come from Brussels?
- Yes.

673
00:41:39,728 --> 00:41:41,153
Did you have a good trip?

674
00:41:41,153 --> 00:41:42,891
Like always.

675
00:41:42,891 --> 00:41:45,847
There were interesting people
in diligence?

676
00:41:45,986 --> 00:41:47,478
Always the same.

677
00:41:48,453 --> 00:41:50,331
Didn't you feel lonely?

678
00:41:50,331 --> 00:41:51,408
Why?

679
00:41:51,408 --> 00:41:53,773
Sometimes, when you travel alone...

680
00:41:55,475 --> 00:41:57,839
No, not my daughter
came with me.

681
00:41:58,257 --> 00:41:59,995
I had a job.

682
00:42:00,447 --> 00:42:01,942
It's a shame.

683
00:42:02,059 --> 00:42:04,736
That tell you that my letter
for Max it worked.

684
00:42:04,736 --> 00:42:05,779
Really?

685
00:42:06,647 --> 00:42:09,394
Oh yeah. Messages arrive
punctual 2 weeks ago.

686
00:42:09,394 --> 00:42:11,759
She will be happy to hear that,

687
00:42:11,759 --> 00:42:14,644
because she runs her office
in Brussels.

688
00:42:15,408 --> 00:42:17,007
But it's impossible!

689
00:42:17,007 --> 00:42:19,963
I also thought,
before seeing her work.

690
00:42:19,963 --> 00:42:22,743
I didn't know, Prof. Magnus.

691
00:42:23,578 --> 00:42:25,072
This is terrible!

692
00:42:25,767 --> 00:42:27,681
What must you think of me!

693
00:42:27,681 --> 00:42:29,558
That's lucky.

694
00:42:29,766 --> 00:42:31,330
But I'm not impartial.

695
00:42:31,330 --> 00:42:33,902
Write to him to thank him.

696
00:42:48,365 --> 00:42:51,457
I knew she was crazy
for you!

697
00:42:54,934 --> 00:42:57,055
She has a quick one.

698
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:04,008
The bag she made.

699
00:43:10,440 --> 00:43:13,776
Fly as fast as possible.

700
00:43:22,747 --> 00:43:25,145
Put them in
next due diligence.

701
00:43:25,388 --> 00:43:27,820
Why do you send them?
to Arnheim?

702
00:43:27,820 --> 00:43:29,525
Why don't they fly?

703
00:43:29,525 --> 00:43:31,749
When it comes loose
a carrier pigeon,

704
00:43:31,749 --> 00:43:34,149
always returns to your home.

705
00:43:35,433 --> 00:43:37,625
And these pigeons' home is here.

706
00:43:37,625 --> 00:43:38,979
I already understand!

707
00:43:41,691 --> 00:43:42,908
Max!

708
00:43:43,355 --> 00:43:44,155
Max!

709
00:43:44,180 --> 00:43:46,090
Did a pigeon arrive?

710
00:43:46,115 --> 00:43:48,966
Silence! I'm in the middle of
composing a poem!

711
00:43:49,096 --> 00:43:51,114
It's desperate!

712
00:44:06,037 --> 00:44:09,234
The answer to the question
that I'm afraid to do

713
00:44:09,259 --> 00:44:11,450
Is it yes or no?

714
00:44:20,558 --> 00:44:22,052
It's no good!

715
00:44:22,505 --> 00:44:25,321
It's better to help her!

716
00:44:25,731 --> 00:44:27,505
Goodbye poetry!

717
00:44:28,416 --> 00:44:32,291
I promise I will dedicate myself
to the pigeons!

718
00:44:35,399 --> 00:44:38,422
Hurry, Lenchen,
He's waiting!

719
00:44:44,267 --> 00:44:48,299
Since he never rests,
brought the food.

720
00:44:48,299 --> 00:44:51,566
- I'm not hungry.
- With the. I watch.

721
00:44:51,671 --> 00:44:53,271
Here it comes!

722
00:45:25,148 --> 00:45:27,340
May I congratulate you?

723
00:45:27,455 --> 00:45:29,229
YES

724
00:45:29,390 --> 00:45:31,998
How did you get it?

725
00:45:46,078 --> 00:45:50,621
The hole between Arnheim
and Brussels is closed!

726
00:45:52,822 --> 00:45:55,359
The lines will work
in a month.

727
00:45:55,359 --> 00:45:58,418
Time passes quickly
when the outcome is uncertain.

728
00:46:01,443 --> 00:46:03,285
It's not fair.

729
00:46:05,330 --> 00:46:07,833
After everything you've done.

730
00:46:08,702 --> 00:46:11,693
Despite prejudices,
the obstacles...

731
00:46:12,329 --> 00:46:14,621
In the end you had won,

732
00:46:14,779 --> 00:46:16,344
and now this...

733
00:46:25,412 --> 00:46:26,768
Lenchen!

734
00:46:27,982 --> 00:46:29,371
What happened?

735
00:46:29,826 --> 00:46:32,294
I found her on the road

736
00:46:32,641 --> 00:46:35,117
killed by a line
by telegraph!

737
00:46:35,596 --> 00:46:39,804
Before, there was nothing there.

738
00:46:41,331 --> 00:46:44,113
One of the workers saw everything.

739
00:46:44,739 --> 00:46:47,276
She has a broken neck!

740
00:47:09,747 --> 00:47:11,972
Back to work, gentlemen.

741
00:47:27,199 --> 00:47:29,630
Crying is no use, dear.

742
00:47:31,404 --> 00:47:32,654
But Lenchen...

743
00:47:32,696 --> 00:47:34,971
Built our future,
wasn't it?

744
00:47:35,507 --> 00:47:37,628
And now, she's dead.

745
00:47:38,045 --> 00:47:40,790
The pigeon mail
died with him.

746
00:47:41,868 --> 00:47:44,059
It's progress, baby.

747
00:47:44,184 --> 00:47:47,590
No one can
oppose progress.

748
00:47:49,050 --> 00:47:51,901
Let this be his epitaph:

749
00:47:51,901 --> 00:47:53,883
"Victim of progress".

750
00:47:58,054 --> 00:48:00,801
The progress
will not destroy us?

751
00:48:00,801 --> 00:48:02,573
Of course not.

752
00:48:02,885 --> 00:48:04,729
Destroyed my business,

753
00:48:04,729 --> 00:48:08,031
but at the same time,
makes the world smaller.

754
00:48:08,448 --> 00:48:10,465
I believe in progress.

755
00:48:10,465 --> 00:48:12,898
How do I believe in a world

756
00:48:13,107 --> 00:48:15,576
what do men
are closer.

757
00:48:15,853 --> 00:48:19,191
The goal of progress
It is knowledge.

758
00:48:19,643 --> 00:48:21,379
And through him,

759
00:48:21,834 --> 00:48:23,050
the truth!

760
00:48:42,448 --> 00:48:44,152
Ah, Max, we're not getting anywhere!

761
00:48:44,152 --> 00:48:45,368
Right.

762
00:48:46,863 --> 00:48:50,166
We should be happy
for earning a living.

763
00:48:50,860 --> 00:48:53,503
But when I go to Paris,

764
00:48:53,503 --> 00:48:55,762
I can't take
my wife!

765
00:48:55,762 --> 00:48:58,195
There are many men
strolling,

766
00:48:59,864 --> 00:49:01,220
except me!

767
00:49:01,672 --> 00:49:03,550
Ida is valid for all women!

768
00:49:03,550 --> 00:49:04,593
Julius, we're in Paris!

769
00:49:05,531 --> 00:49:08,799
Stop praising your wife.

770
00:49:08,938 --> 00:49:12,240
My friends wouldn't understand it.

771
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:13,979
You should be ashamed of your friends!

772
00:49:13,979 --> 00:49:18,150
I can't offer anything else
with my salary!

773
00:49:18,150 --> 00:49:20,409
I'm a director,
employee, everything!

774
00:49:20,409 --> 00:49:23,608
Ida is not in charge of the
London office?

775
00:49:23,608 --> 00:49:25,590
She has you.

776
00:49:25,590 --> 00:49:27,398
You're right, Max.

777
00:49:27,398 --> 00:49:29,136
There they are!

778
00:49:31,848 --> 00:49:34,316
Yvonne, how about it? Jeanette!

779
00:49:35,392 --> 00:49:37,410
Let me introduce you to my friend, Mr. Reuter.

780
00:49:52,081 --> 00:49:55,453
The news is not very
encouraging, right?

781
00:49:56,147 --> 00:49:58,442
War, always war!

782
00:49:58,477 --> 00:50:01,361
During my life,
it has always been like that.

783
00:50:01,361 --> 00:50:03,066
And I'm already old!

784
00:50:03,066 --> 00:50:05,047
You have seen many changes!

785
00:50:05,047 --> 00:50:06,438
Yes sir. Lots of.

786
00:50:06,818 --> 00:50:11,234
But most of all, the world
advances faster and faster.

787
00:50:11,525 --> 00:50:13,403
Everything arrives so quickly!

788
00:50:13,403 --> 00:50:16,706
My newspapers don't have
more than a day late

789
00:50:16,706 --> 00:50:18,409
and they don't tell us anything.

790
00:50:18,409 --> 00:50:20,426
Sevastopol was taken,

791
00:50:20,426 --> 00:50:23,624
our troops are in Crimea
willing to kill.

792
00:50:24,562 --> 00:50:28,177
We have to read what is hidden.
See here below.

793
00:50:28,282 --> 00:50:29,533
Are you here?

794
00:50:29,533 --> 00:50:33,357
"There will be a meeting
between the Allied General Staff

795
00:50:33,357 --> 00:50:36,035
and the Russian generals."

796
00:50:37,633 --> 00:50:39,093
Is it a sign of peace?

797
00:50:39,093 --> 00:50:41,770
You'll know in a week.

798
00:50:41,770 --> 00:50:42,918
Why?

799
00:50:42,918 --> 00:50:45,629
Louis Napoleon will speak
to deputies.

800
00:50:45,629 --> 00:50:48,063
He will announce peace himself.

801
00:50:49,905 --> 00:50:52,651
The whole world waits
this speech!

802
00:50:52,651 --> 00:50:54,634
The whole world...

803
00:51:03,114 --> 00:51:06,729
Why does Paris always do
Tremble, my heart?

804
00:51:07,703 --> 00:51:09,548
Excuse me!

805
00:51:10,728 --> 00:51:12,293
What's up?

806
00:51:12,537 --> 00:51:13,996
I'm an idiot!

807
00:51:13,996 --> 00:51:15,422
The biggest!

808
00:51:15,422 --> 00:51:17,646
- It's incredible!!!
- Sit down.

809
00:51:19,072 --> 00:51:20,776
- Let's go!
- I can't go.

810
00:51:21,019 --> 00:51:22,269
One moment!

811
00:51:22,269 --> 00:51:24,217
- Will you come back?
- Wait for me.

812
00:51:29,257 --> 00:51:32,351
What's up?
Got crazy?

813
00:51:32,629 --> 00:51:34,402
Worse! I'm an idiot!

814
00:51:34,402 --> 00:51:35,655
You already said it.

815
00:51:35,655 --> 00:51:37,357
You don't understand, Max.

816
00:51:37,985 --> 00:51:40,416
- I should have thought years ago.
- What?

817
00:51:41,530 --> 00:51:45,075
The news!
It's the most important thing in the world!

818
00:51:45,075 --> 00:51:48,657
With the telegraph, the words
they fly at the speed of light.

819
00:51:48,657 --> 00:51:50,394
What does it have to do with you?

820
00:51:50,394 --> 00:51:51,402
Precisely.

821
00:51:51,402 --> 00:51:54,635
Every city in Europe
It is served by the telegraph.

822
00:51:54,768 --> 00:51:57,480
Why not broadcast the
news

823
00:51:57,515 --> 00:51:59,670
as far as messages
personal?

824
00:51:59,670 --> 00:52:02,763
How would you get
all the news?

825
00:52:02,763 --> 00:52:04,781
We have correspondents
all over Europe, don't we?

826
00:52:05,042 --> 00:52:06,014
What about?

827
00:52:06,100 --> 00:52:09,265
They are not reporters.

828
00:52:09,473 --> 00:52:11,559
They are in the heart
of an organization.

829
00:52:11,768 --> 00:52:15,782
You could go visit them
and check your competence.

830
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:18,547
We need good reporters.

831
00:52:18,547 --> 00:52:20,772
- Let's start soon.
- One moment!

832
00:52:21,432 --> 00:52:23,171
It's a radical idea.

833
00:52:23,171 --> 00:52:26,056
The telegraph works
since years ago.

834
00:52:26,056 --> 00:52:29,253
But no one uses it
for the latest news!

835
00:52:29,253 --> 00:52:30,993
There's a reason for that.

836
00:52:30,993 --> 00:52:34,955
Nobody ever thought about that.

837
00:52:35,199 --> 00:52:38,432
Max, let's telegraph news!

838
00:52:43,334 --> 00:52:46,323
The world will be up to date
fast enough.

839
00:52:46,836 --> 00:52:48,320
Allow me not
be in agreement.

840
00:52:48,377 --> 00:52:51,742
London will be informed
24 hours later!

841
00:52:52,727 --> 00:52:54,773
Without giving advice
to His Majesty,

842
00:52:54,909 --> 00:52:59,117
the best thing would be for you to know
The English react quickly!

843
00:53:00,240 --> 00:53:01,762
What do you propose?

844
00:53:02,036 --> 00:53:06,286
I will reserve the telegraph
between here and London.

845
00:53:06,670 --> 00:53:08,895
Telegraph the speech
to London?

846
00:53:08,920 --> 00:53:09,789
Yes sir.

847
00:53:10,554 --> 00:53:14,066
No one will stop you,
once the speech has been delivered.

848
00:53:14,841 --> 00:53:16,125
Sir.

849
00:53:17,367 --> 00:53:19,140
Yes but...

850
00:53:19,140 --> 00:53:21,435
It will be too late, sir.

851
00:53:21,435 --> 00:53:25,155
Time will be wasted translating
the speech into English.

852
00:53:25,344 --> 00:53:26,962
Sorry, there is no other solution.

853
00:53:26,962 --> 00:53:29,013
Yes, there is, sir.

854
00:53:29,013 --> 00:53:32,108
I need to have the
speech before.

855
00:53:33,324 --> 00:53:36,557
- This has never been done.
- Naturally.

856
00:53:37,010 --> 00:53:39,299
And no speech
It was never telegraphed.

857
00:53:39,767 --> 00:53:43,103
One innovation creates another.
It's progress.

858
00:53:43,456 --> 00:53:47,322
The world must know quickly
what the leaders say,

859
00:53:47,447 --> 00:53:49,149
how they decide their destiny.

860
00:53:49,360 --> 00:53:52,331
And the leaders will know right away
people's opinions.

861
00:53:52,653 --> 00:53:56,825
I would like to create
a new genre of journalism.

862
00:53:57,646 --> 00:54:02,055
And they will know that Louis Napoleon
participated in this creation.

863
00:54:02,055 --> 00:54:03,863
Excellent idea.

864
00:54:03,984 --> 00:54:04,952
His majesty!

865
00:54:05,021 --> 00:54:08,916
I would like to know more about
his "new journalism".

866
00:54:09,629 --> 00:54:11,053
Follow me.

867
00:54:18,423 --> 00:54:19,292
The hotel.

868
00:54:19,398 --> 00:54:20,378
Yes sir.

869
00:54:21,374 --> 00:54:21,971
So?

870
00:54:22,081 --> 00:54:23,889
- They agree.
- Formidable!

871
00:54:24,030 --> 00:54:25,074
On one condition.

872
00:54:25,113 --> 00:54:27,122
Let us wait for
beginning of the speech.

873
00:54:27,176 --> 00:54:30,119
- Will we have enough time?
- If you book the telegraph now.

874
00:54:30,144 --> 00:54:31,187
- Who? I?
- Yes, you.

875
00:54:31,430 --> 00:54:35,122
Nonetheless,
I will prepare everything in London.

876
00:54:39,335 --> 00:54:40,341
Something else?

877
00:54:40,687 --> 00:54:43,662
Lord Palmerston
canceled your appointment.

878
00:54:43,747 --> 00:54:46,633
The man thinks he is more important
than the Times of London?

879
00:54:46,766 --> 00:54:49,303
You will regret it. Anything else?

880
00:54:49,328 --> 00:54:50,863
Mr. Reuter is waiting for you.

881
00:54:51,093 --> 00:54:52,593
I don't have time.

882
00:54:52,641 --> 00:54:54,553
He insists and waits for you.

883
00:54:56,041 --> 00:54:57,642
I will be back in an hour.

884
00:54:57,642 --> 00:54:58,822
Mr. Delane?

885
00:54:59,150 --> 00:55:02,076
- It must be Rooter.
- Julius Reuter.

886
00:55:02,101 --> 00:55:04,543
Forgive me, sir.
I have an important appointment.

887
00:55:04,568 --> 00:55:07,349
You know my proposal.

888
00:55:07,529 --> 00:55:10,066
- But....
- Let me talk.

889
00:55:10,091 --> 00:55:14,193
The Times already has reporters
who write the news.

890
00:55:14,218 --> 00:55:16,286
But that costs a fortune.

891
00:55:16,354 --> 00:55:17,953
You're wasting your time,
it's mine.

892
00:55:18,809 --> 00:55:21,728
The Times will not run
this risk.

893
00:55:21,728 --> 00:55:24,545
Try one month for free.

894
00:55:24,545 --> 00:55:27,116
The Times has its ways,
Mr. Rooter.

895
00:55:27,116 --> 00:55:28,650
- Reuter, Reuter!
- And more,

896
00:55:28,853 --> 00:55:31,706
the idea of ​​a news agency
It's absurd.

897
00:55:31,706 --> 00:55:34,313
We want exclusivity

898
00:55:34,579 --> 00:55:35,934
to be the first!

899
00:55:35,959 --> 00:55:36,927
This is journalism!

900
00:55:37,129 --> 00:55:38,589
The news must
be fresh.

901
00:55:38,589 --> 00:55:42,102
Even a newspaper like the Times
cannot support exclusive use
of the telegraph.

902
00:55:42,345 --> 00:55:43,872
If you use...

903
00:55:47,393 --> 00:55:48,678
I understand.

904
00:55:48,913 --> 00:55:52,564
But we already have one
service abroad.

905
00:55:52,564 --> 00:55:54,311
Which costs £40 a month.

906
00:55:54,366 --> 00:55:58,018
I propose for 30 pounds.

907
00:55:58,589 --> 00:55:59,964
It's a huge risk.

908
00:56:00,171 --> 00:56:02,292
Try one month for free.

909
00:56:02,750 --> 00:56:03,863
Free?

910
00:56:03,934 --> 00:56:05,808
I just ask that you use the name Reuter,

911
00:56:05,906 --> 00:56:08,879
And use your name as the first customer.

912
00:56:10,535 --> 00:56:12,446
That seems fair.

913
00:56:12,588 --> 00:56:15,371
God bless the Scots!

914
00:56:15,811 --> 00:56:17,424
The Advertiser was the first.

915
00:56:17,479 --> 00:56:20,158
Then it was the Post,
the Herald and the News.

916
00:56:20,376 --> 00:56:22,044
- The Times?
- Not yet.

917
00:56:22,192 --> 00:56:24,036
Here's the whole story.

918
00:56:24,304 --> 00:56:28,022
It will be very expensive to rent
the cable from Paris to London.

919
00:56:28,022 --> 00:56:30,040
We don't have that sum.

920
00:56:30,040 --> 00:56:33,412
The money given by newspapers
help us.

921
00:56:33,550 --> 00:56:35,636
- We won't have anything this month.
- What?

922
00:56:35,706 --> 00:56:38,346
I offered the service free of charge
for them to accept.

923
00:56:38,462 --> 00:56:39,818
I'm sorry, Ida.

924
00:56:39,982 --> 00:56:41,999
- Why?
- Stay!

925
00:56:41,999 --> 00:56:45,197
I'll go before I lose
calm and a friend.

926
00:56:47,998 --> 00:56:49,319
As?

927
00:56:49,344 --> 00:56:53,586
- You are completely crazy.
- Perhaps.

928
00:56:53,804 --> 00:56:56,028
Even if it covers the
whole world,

929
00:56:56,169 --> 00:56:59,126
and it works,
the Times will reject it!

930
00:56:59,195 --> 00:57:03,540
These newspapers accepted it for free.

931
00:57:03,818 --> 00:57:05,382
The Times isn't even free!

932
00:57:05,382 --> 00:57:08,824
Every cent you receive
it will be for expenses.

933
00:57:08,824 --> 00:57:12,057
And God knows
who received little.

934
00:57:12,204 --> 00:57:14,638
Your wife deserves better!

935
00:57:15,055 --> 00:57:17,766
Can you lend me
1000 pounds?

936
00:57:17,766 --> 00:57:18,808
As?

937
00:57:20,548 --> 00:57:24,301
We provide you with stock quotes
6 years ago.

938
00:57:24,736 --> 00:57:28,908
He made a fortune,
as well as others,

939
00:57:28,908 --> 00:57:31,271
Thanks to our reliability.

940
00:57:31,296 --> 00:57:36,059
For the first time, I find myself obliged
asking him for something.

941
00:57:36,243 --> 00:57:38,537
- But...
- I know what I do.

942
00:57:38,537 --> 00:57:41,145
Just say yes or no.

943
00:57:42,089 --> 00:57:44,557
- When do you need it?
- Tomorrow.

944
00:57:45,452 --> 00:57:47,052
You will have the money!

945
00:57:47,253 --> 00:57:48,573
Thank you, Sir Randolph.

946
00:57:49,234 --> 00:57:51,215
I won't forget him.

947
00:57:55,873 --> 00:57:58,168
Sir Randolph doesn't like it
of the idea?

948
00:57:58,168 --> 00:57:59,732
I don't think so.

949
00:58:00,149 --> 00:58:01,923
That won't come.

950
00:58:01,923 --> 00:58:04,253
You will have to ask for a loan.

951
00:58:04,253 --> 00:58:05,781
I already did.

952
00:58:05,781 --> 00:58:07,173
How did you borrow it?

953
00:58:07,867 --> 00:58:09,085
Dear,

954
00:58:09,085 --> 00:58:11,657
Let's take a big risk.

955
00:58:11,726 --> 00:58:14,195
It's all or nothing.

956
00:58:16,037 --> 00:58:18,088
You believe in this idea.

957
00:58:18,296 --> 00:58:20,418
The world is still very big.

958
00:58:20,798 --> 00:58:22,642
Let's make it smaller.

959
00:58:29,491 --> 00:58:30,569
And now,

960
00:58:31,264 --> 00:58:34,461
since the news
are under our dominion,

961
00:58:35,228 --> 00:58:38,599
we have to include "news"
in the name of our company.

962
00:58:39,015 --> 00:58:42,839
Yes, Reuters Agency
or something similar.

963
00:58:42,839 --> 00:58:44,613
Or something like that.

964
00:58:45,413 --> 00:58:49,896
The director of the Reuters Agency,
or whatever name you choose,

965
00:58:50,730 --> 00:58:52,748
must be aware
current affairs, right?

966
00:58:52,748 --> 00:58:54,902
As much as possible.

967
00:58:54,902 --> 00:58:59,353
Here is the first task
to perpetuate in our records.

968
00:59:00,221 --> 00:59:03,700
This is nothing exceptional,

969
00:59:04,049 --> 00:59:07,317
but it will always
a good effect.

970
00:59:07,768 --> 00:59:08,951
What?

971
00:59:10,583 --> 00:59:11,663
Know...

972
00:59:11,906 --> 00:59:13,818
from a safe source...

973
00:59:14,062 --> 00:59:15,555
that Julius Reuter,

974
00:59:15,773 --> 00:59:18,415
president and founder

975
00:59:18,589 --> 00:59:21,196
from the Reuters Agency...

976
00:59:21,915 --> 00:59:23,915
Yes?

977
00:59:27,106 --> 00:59:29,194
will be a father.

978
00:59:35,347 --> 00:59:37,015
I? Father?

979
00:59:37,745 --> 00:59:40,109
The Reuter agency is always reliable.

980
00:59:40,734 --> 00:59:43,898
Ida, it's wonderful!

981
00:59:44,767 --> 00:59:48,208
It's the most beautiful news
of the world!

982
00:59:54,291 --> 00:59:56,898
- What are you going to do?
- I'll wire Max.

983
00:59:56,898 --> 00:59:58,395
The business is different now.

984
00:59:58,833 --> 01:00:03,145
We cannot allow
take risks now.

985
01:00:03,597 --> 01:00:05,996
Not with a baby.

986
01:00:06,204 --> 01:00:08,533
From now on, the baby is
the most important thing.

987
01:00:11,974 --> 01:00:14,548
It will be exactly as planned.

988
01:00:16,598 --> 01:00:19,205
We will go on the adventure together.

989
01:00:20,110 --> 01:00:21,604
The three.

990
01:00:41,245 --> 01:00:44,235
Gentlemen Senators
and deputies!

991
01:00:45,217 --> 01:00:46,983
In our last interview,

992
01:00:46,983 --> 01:00:49,867
the circumstances were complex.

993
01:00:49,867 --> 01:00:52,995
The allied troops
were being closed

994
01:00:53,170 --> 01:00:57,237
with an obstinacy that left
glimpse doubts in his final victory.

995
01:01:00,679 --> 01:01:02,869
A message to the Reuters Agency
from London.

996
01:01:02,869 --> 01:01:03,911
I was waiting for you.

997
01:01:03,911 --> 01:01:07,352
I hope too
let the emperor begin.

998
01:01:07,561 --> 01:01:11,316
The emperor! That's why it was rented
the cable for an hour!

999
01:01:35,443 --> 01:01:37,180
The Mourning Herald!

1000
01:01:39,892 --> 01:01:42,813
The proclamation of peace!

1001
01:01:45,629 --> 01:01:47,609
Special edition!

1002
01:02:00,021 --> 01:02:03,567
I need to write to my father...
and Geller too!

1003
01:02:03,567 --> 01:02:05,165
I wish they were here.

1004
01:02:06,556 --> 01:02:07,705
Julius!

1005
01:02:07,705 --> 01:02:10,937
It is a triumph that
transforms journalism!

1006
01:02:10,937 --> 01:02:13,509
It's a revolution for
the written press

1007
01:02:16,048 --> 01:02:18,237
Let us not exaggerate, my friend.

1008
01:02:18,237 --> 01:02:22,409
This man brings the news
of peace to a world at war

1009
01:02:22,434 --> 01:02:24,425
without an "I already told you".

1010
01:02:25,641 --> 01:02:27,623
I love him even more.

1011
01:02:27,866 --> 01:02:31,899
The Times! Special edition!

1012
01:02:34,819 --> 01:02:37,496
How did you get the
Times of this speech?

1013
01:02:38,296 --> 01:02:39,617
I sent it.

1014
01:02:39,617 --> 01:02:42,605
You told me that Delane
refused to subscribe.

1015
01:02:42,779 --> 01:02:43,893
He will accept.

1016
01:02:44,693 --> 01:02:48,063
Not Delane. He's very stubborn.

1017
01:02:48,141 --> 01:02:50,393
He could have been ridiculed if he hadn't...

1018
01:02:50,845 --> 01:02:51,855
Mr. Reuters!

1019
01:02:52,168 --> 01:02:52,897
Yes?

1020
01:02:52,897 --> 01:02:54,565
Mr. Delane would like to see you.

1021
01:02:54,565 --> 01:02:55,782
Delane!

1022
01:02:57,876 --> 01:02:59,989
- Come in.
- Yes sir.

1023
01:03:03,599 --> 01:03:05,239
I want to cry.

1024
01:03:06,162 --> 01:03:09,703
Wait for Delane to leave,
we will cry together.

1025
01:03:09,784 --> 01:03:11,349
I leave them alone.

1026
01:03:14,151 --> 01:03:15,923
- Sir Randolph!
- How are you?

1027
01:03:16,619 --> 01:03:17,837
Mr. Rooter...

1028
01:03:17,837 --> 01:03:19,574
Reuter, Mr. Delane.

1029
01:03:19,574 --> 01:03:21,322
Forgive me, Mr. Reuter.
I would like...

1030
01:03:21,352 --> 01:03:23,986
- I want to introduce you to my wife.
- My respects.

1031
01:03:24,124 --> 01:03:26,245
- I want...
- Please sit.

1032
01:03:32,854 --> 01:03:35,670
The Times is grateful,
Mr. Reuters.

1033
01:03:35,670 --> 01:03:37,790
For the first time,
our newspaper

1034
01:03:37,790 --> 01:03:40,781
publish a news
from an external company.

1035
01:03:43,491 --> 01:03:45,334
"The emperor's speech..."

1036
01:03:45,578 --> 01:03:48,818
"received by Reuters Agency."

1037
01:03:52,123 --> 01:03:55,043
It's an immense honor,
Mr. Delane.

1038
01:03:55,312 --> 01:03:57,015
Come on, say it!

1039
01:03:57,293 --> 01:04:01,290
"Delane, what an idiot you are."
I deserve it!

1040
01:04:02,021 --> 01:04:03,794
Our agency is accurate

1041
01:04:03,794 --> 01:04:05,462
and impartial.

1042
01:04:05,727 --> 01:04:10,421
Only the present counts,
the past is ancient history.

1043
01:04:11,045 --> 01:04:13,620
What news
bring, Mr. Delane?

1044
01:04:17,583 --> 01:04:18,659
Mr. Reuters.

1045
01:04:19,111 --> 01:04:22,170
You can add the Times
It's your customer list.

1046
01:04:23,178 --> 01:04:25,064
Thanks,
Mr Delane!

1047
01:04:25,646 --> 01:04:27,210
I...

1048
01:04:28,742 --> 01:04:31,035
I'm afraid I won't be able to wait.

1049
01:04:44,315 --> 01:04:45,950
Lenchen!

1050
01:05:27,840 --> 01:05:31,107
"An honor that never
renounce.

1051
01:05:31,107 --> 01:05:34,097
"Who always rejects.

1052
01:05:34,097 --> 01:05:37,921
"Which is called by error
Rooter.

1053
01:05:38,756 --> 01:05:41,363
"Weave your skein

1054
01:05:41,467 --> 01:05:44,421
"around the world where
we inhabit.

1055
01:05:44,421 --> 01:05:48,559
"The oceans will murmur your name.

1056
01:05:49,984 --> 01:05:52,625
"That for the whole world,

1057
01:05:52,625 --> 01:05:55,513
"Be a guide, a tutor.

1058
01:05:56,590 --> 01:05:58,328
"May you be blessed

1059
01:05:58,328 --> 01:06:02,187
"as much as Reuters
as much as Rooter."

1060
01:06:05,419 --> 01:06:06,845
Amazing!

1061
01:06:07,887 --> 01:06:09,730
But where did you learn this?

1062
01:06:09,973 --> 01:06:11,295
Are you good for anything?

1063
01:06:12,859 --> 01:06:15,118
It's just a small thing...

1064
01:06:15,536 --> 01:06:17,518
published by Gazeta
of Saint-James.

1065
01:06:17,969 --> 01:06:21,898
All Europe speaks
from you, Julius.

1066
01:06:22,837 --> 01:06:26,729
Got your name in the newspapers
more often than anyone.

1067
01:06:27,390 --> 01:06:30,797
Baby, you recited
perfectly.

1068
01:06:31,457 --> 01:06:33,439
It's time to go to bed.

1069
01:06:35,278 --> 01:06:36,669
Say goodnight to dad.

1070
01:06:36,961 --> 01:06:41,597
Father. My name will also be in us
newspapers when I'm older?

1071
01:06:42,438 --> 01:06:44,559
One day, you will take my place,

1072
01:06:44,559 --> 01:06:46,540
and Reuter will be you.

1073
01:06:46,540 --> 01:06:50,364
I want that to be the only reason
to get your name in the newspapers!

1074
01:06:51,214 --> 01:06:52,891
- Goodnight.
- To the bed!

1075
01:06:53,164 --> 01:06:54,415
At your service.

1076
01:06:54,449 --> 01:06:58,100
At your service, Mr. Reuter.
He is his father's son.

1077
01:06:58,517 --> 01:06:59,525
Julius.

1078
01:06:59,664 --> 01:07:01,994
What a beautiful surprise!

1079
01:07:02,237 --> 01:07:03,940
My respects, ma'am.

1080
01:07:06,165 --> 01:07:08,459
I'll sit by the fire.

1081
01:07:08,459 --> 01:07:10,023
It's cold tonight.

1082
01:07:10,023 --> 01:07:11,241
Going for coffee?

1083
01:07:12,003 --> 01:07:13,073
Thank you very much.

1084
01:07:14,611 --> 01:07:16,525
I always liked your coffee.

1085
01:07:20,070 --> 01:07:21,218
Julius.

1086
01:07:22,851 --> 01:07:24,625
get ready to
a fight.

1087
01:07:24,625 --> 01:07:25,770
Fight?

1088
01:07:26,641 --> 01:07:29,875
Against the Anglo-Irish Company
of Telegraphs.

1089
01:07:30,291 --> 01:07:31,716
I work with them.

1090
01:07:31,716 --> 01:07:33,002
Exactly.

1091
01:07:33,454 --> 01:07:35,124
Hence their idea.

1092
01:07:35,273 --> 01:07:37,418
You can't ban me
to use your lines.

1093
01:07:37,418 --> 01:07:40,929
But you can build a
for their exclusive use.

1094
01:07:41,034 --> 01:07:42,598
They wouldn't!

1095
01:07:42,691 --> 01:07:44,394
They already did.

1096
01:07:45,507 --> 01:07:48,704
A private line from Roches Point
to Queenstown.

1097
01:08:04,841 --> 01:08:07,519
Where is Roches Point?

1098
01:08:10,884 --> 01:08:11,753
Here.

1099
01:08:12,754 --> 01:08:16,855
This is where the US mail arrives
and then go to Queenstown.

1100
01:08:17,349 --> 01:08:19,748
From there, we ship it to London.

1101
01:08:20,200 --> 01:08:21,905
Tell me, Julius,

1102
01:08:22,738 --> 01:08:26,284
how long it takes
your messenger to Queenstown?

1103
01:08:26,585 --> 01:08:27,767
2 hours.

1104
01:08:29,540 --> 01:08:31,833
You will win for 2 hours.

1105
01:08:32,354 --> 01:08:35,971
They built this line in secret
a few weeks ago.

1106
01:08:36,389 --> 01:08:40,734
Even I ignored it until I
proposed their services.

1107
01:08:41,359 --> 01:08:42,818
From when?

1108
01:08:43,235 --> 01:08:44,801
Tomorrow.

1109
01:08:46,573 --> 01:08:48,625
This is the end of the Reuters Agency.

1110
01:08:56,900 --> 01:08:59,993
I want to cancel immediately
my contract.

1111
01:08:59,993 --> 01:09:02,079
If you wait until Mr. Reuter arrives.

1112
01:09:02,079 --> 01:09:03,373
It's useless.

1113
01:09:03,522 --> 01:09:07,607
Why should I pay for news
who arrive 2 hours late?

1114
01:09:08,023 --> 01:09:09,675
- Hello, Grant.
- How are you?

1115
01:09:17,236 --> 01:09:19,633
Max! Could you see him for a moment?

1116
01:09:19,633 --> 01:09:21,894
Of course you do, Mr. Grant.

1117
01:09:23,945 --> 01:09:27,600
It's the fifth today,
Isn't that Bruce?

1118
01:09:27,749 --> 01:09:28,605
It's true.

1119
01:09:28,630 --> 01:09:30,229
- And 3 yesterday?
- Yes.

1120
01:09:30,705 --> 01:09:33,261
If cancellations continue,

1121
01:09:33,339 --> 01:09:35,715
I'm looking for another job.
Isn't it?

1122
01:09:35,879 --> 01:09:37,409
Wrong.

1123
01:09:37,409 --> 01:09:41,164
I bet you'll never make it
overtake Reuter.

1124
01:09:41,373 --> 01:09:42,588
Thanks, Bruce.

1125
01:09:44,466 --> 01:09:47,977
Attention, it could take
part of your bet.

1126
01:09:48,081 --> 01:09:49,646
Everything you want.

1127
01:09:49,646 --> 01:09:51,210
You are kind.

1128
01:09:52,949 --> 01:09:54,870
I need someone
in New York.

1129
01:09:55,059 --> 01:09:57,468
Someone trustworthy.

1130
01:09:57,773 --> 01:09:59,377
- Would you go?
- Clear.

1131
01:09:59,410 --> 01:10:00,077
Great.

1132
01:10:00,124 --> 01:10:01,709
Try to understand...

1133
01:10:01,709 --> 01:10:03,517
- Oh, Julius!
- Nice to see you.

1134
01:10:03,517 --> 01:10:06,228
It won't be much longer.

1135
01:10:06,228 --> 01:10:07,957
I know.
I know.

1136
01:10:08,698 --> 01:10:11,269
The Anglo-Irish beat us
for 2 hours in London.

1137
01:10:11,955 --> 01:10:15,268
Many of our customers
they abandon us.

1138
01:10:15,268 --> 01:10:17,562
- How do you know?
- That's what you should do!

1139
01:10:17,562 --> 01:10:20,863
They pay. If they are not
Satisfied, they leave.

1140
01:10:23,064 --> 01:10:25,070
Don't put on that face!

1141
01:10:25,070 --> 01:10:27,016
I'm not finished yet.

1142
01:10:27,016 --> 01:10:30,597
Your contract is
temporarily suspended.

1143
01:10:30,597 --> 01:10:34,317
You will continue to receive free
our messages

1144
01:10:34,317 --> 01:10:37,377
until the Reuters Agency
return to the first position.

1145
01:10:38,559 --> 01:10:40,749
Inform our customers.

1146
01:10:40,749 --> 01:10:42,486
You can't do that!

1147
01:10:42,486 --> 01:10:44,851
In time of war
We cannot accept defeat.

1148
01:10:45,130 --> 01:10:46,971
Bravo, Reuter!

1149
01:10:46,971 --> 01:10:50,100
I hope you win
the Anglo-Irish!

1150
01:10:55,280 --> 01:10:57,886
Here's one to cheer
by Reuters Agency.

1151
01:10:59,104 --> 01:11:01,921
Where were you? Have you seen Ida yet?

1152
01:11:01,921 --> 01:11:02,825
Not yet.

1153
01:11:02,825 --> 01:11:04,561
Didn't you write?!

1154
01:11:04,770 --> 01:11:06,370
Is Sir Randolph in London?

1155
01:11:06,370 --> 01:11:08,143
He is with Ida.

1156
01:11:08,143 --> 01:11:11,444
He called when she got a letter
of Anglo-Irish.

1157
01:11:11,931 --> 01:11:13,046
What they want?

1158
01:11:13,046 --> 01:11:14,678
It's better to read the letter.

1159
01:11:14,817 --> 01:11:16,904
- Where is it?
- Ida has it.

1160
01:11:18,676 --> 01:11:22,466
"In these circumstances.
we think it's very generous

1161
01:11:22,466 --> 01:11:25,421
offer 20,000 pounds
for your company."

1162
01:11:25,421 --> 01:11:28,307
- At 20,000 pounds!
- The offer is reasonable.

1163
01:11:28,307 --> 01:11:29,800
They have you where they want.

1164
01:11:29,800 --> 01:11:32,199
That's what they think!

1165
01:11:33,353 --> 01:11:36,668
"We propose what remains
as director

1166
01:11:36,920 --> 01:11:38,753
with a salary that will be negotiated."

1167
01:11:38,778 --> 01:11:39,862
What audacity!

1168
01:11:40,433 --> 01:11:43,005
They want to steal my company!

1169
01:11:44,082 --> 01:11:46,238
The money will not be
a problem.

1170
01:11:46,238 --> 01:11:47,488
That pleases you, doesn't it?

1171
01:11:47,488 --> 01:11:48,775
I'm sorry, but...

1172
01:11:50,340 --> 01:11:52,633
You could retire...

1173
01:11:52,956 --> 01:11:54,972
Idleness?!

1174
01:11:55,487 --> 01:11:57,052
This is my life!

1175
01:11:57,295 --> 01:11:59,798
They might as well bury me!

1176
01:12:00,006 --> 01:12:01,642
Start a newspaper!

1177
01:12:01,642 --> 01:12:03,969
No, I have no opinions to sell,
just news.

1178
01:12:04,212 --> 01:12:06,577
What are you going to do, Julius?

1179
01:12:11,339 --> 01:12:14,468
- Tidy subject.
- That doesn't answer Ida.

1180
01:12:14,468 --> 01:12:17,528
I will respond if you lend me
5,000 pounds.

1181
01:12:17,528 --> 01:12:18,987
5,000 pounds?!

1182
01:12:20,587 --> 01:12:22,012
It's best you know:

1183
01:12:22,012 --> 01:12:24,099
I don't have a penny.

1184
01:12:24,872 --> 01:12:27,122
Maybe it needs a lot more.

1185
01:12:27,462 --> 01:12:30,660
- Do you want to take a risk?
- I have little.

1186
01:12:30,739 --> 01:12:33,484
I invested a lot in the stock market.

1187
01:12:33,671 --> 01:12:37,874
The Civil War
continues in America.

1188
01:12:38,093 --> 01:12:40,194
What if the South loses?

1189
01:12:40,402 --> 01:12:42,663
I would be in a delicate situation.

1190
01:12:42,663 --> 01:12:44,365
Take cover.

1191
01:12:44,365 --> 01:12:46,520
At least 5,000 pounds.

1192
01:12:48,259 --> 01:12:50,309
You are fearsome, Julius.

1193
01:12:51,236 --> 01:12:52,611
Accordingly.

1194
01:12:52,862 --> 01:12:53,649
Thanks.

1195
01:12:54,989 --> 01:12:56,617
We can start!

1196
01:13:11,830 --> 01:13:15,549
Julius.
We'll never make it in this weather!

1197
01:13:15,549 --> 01:13:16,696
Every day counts, Max.

1198
01:13:16,696 --> 01:13:20,172
Men already work
12 hours a day.

1199
01:13:20,172 --> 01:13:23,336
Put in another shift.
Let's work 24 hours a day!

1200
01:13:33,382 --> 01:13:34,947
More cable!

1201
01:13:40,614 --> 01:13:43,047
80 km is a lot!

1202
01:13:43,430 --> 01:13:46,002
In 2 weeks we will be finished.

1203
01:13:46,002 --> 01:13:48,087
Working night and day.

1204
01:13:48,331 --> 01:13:51,495
And if we really end
in 2 weeks?

1205
01:13:51,840 --> 01:13:55,074
The mail boat
It doesn't stop at Crookshaven.

1206
01:13:55,074 --> 01:13:56,291
It has to stop!

1207
01:13:56,291 --> 01:13:57,994
How will we get the mail?

1208
01:13:57,994 --> 01:14:00,149
I'll think about it, Max.

1209
01:14:25,318 --> 01:14:27,751
- It works!
- It's dry.

1210
01:14:28,238 --> 01:14:28,795
Bruce...

1211
01:14:29,166 --> 01:14:31,773
You will be my agent
in America.

1212
01:14:44,820 --> 01:14:48,539
"Tell my daughter
in my presence!"

1213
01:14:49,966 --> 01:14:53,684
"I offer everything I have:
my heart and my hands."

1214
01:14:53,788 --> 01:14:55,910
"Go to your room, sweetie."

1215
01:14:55,910 --> 01:14:58,343
"Yes, mother.
You bastard!”

1216
01:15:00,498 --> 01:15:03,531
"I know you don't know
politeness."

1217
01:15:03,628 --> 01:15:07,172
"It's the only excuse
for your impertinence."

1218
01:15:07,589 --> 01:15:10,127
"I don't know any manners, do I?"

1219
01:15:12,804 --> 01:15:14,785
Lincoln is assassinated!

1220
01:15:17,323 --> 01:15:20,470
Please contact immediately
the mail boat!

1221
01:15:24,241 --> 01:15:26,327
New York Reuters Agency!

1222
01:15:26,779 --> 01:15:29,107
The boat leaves from New York
tomorrow morning.

1223
01:15:34,046 --> 01:15:35,226
The Times of London!

1224
01:15:35,226 --> 01:15:36,965
The Anglo-Irish!

1225
01:15:36,965 --> 01:15:39,433
United States Embassy!

1226
01:15:41,831 --> 01:15:44,126
Reuters Agency in London!

1227
01:15:52,678 --> 01:15:54,730
Sit down, Mr. Randolph.

1228
01:15:54,938 --> 01:15:57,058
A cup of tea, thank you.

1229
01:15:57,058 --> 01:15:58,900
What are you afraid of?

1230
01:15:58,900 --> 01:16:00,987
- Have you been reading newspapers?
- Yes.

1231
01:16:02,183 --> 01:16:04,408
The market turns against me.

1232
01:16:05,625 --> 01:16:09,518
I will pay dearly if I am mistaken about
the result of the American War.

1233
01:16:09,727 --> 01:16:11,744
Lincoln is not a monster.

1234
01:16:11,744 --> 01:16:13,238
It's smart.

1235
01:16:13,238 --> 01:16:17,898
Investing in the South is good as long as
Lincoln is president.

1236
01:16:18,525 --> 01:16:19,602
I expect!

1237
01:16:19,602 --> 01:16:22,801
However, the market is
It's on the verge of collapse.

1238
01:16:23,947 --> 01:16:27,424
I'm screwed, Julius,
very contrived.

1239
01:16:28,777 --> 01:16:31,176
You want your 5,000 pounds.

1240
01:16:31,870 --> 01:16:33,888
Thank you for saying this for me.

1241
01:16:34,860 --> 01:16:36,947
I don't have them.

1242
01:16:39,205 --> 01:16:41,186
You have to recover them.

1243
01:16:43,238 --> 01:16:45,150
In a few days.

1244
01:16:53,980 --> 01:16:55,544
The mail boat!

1245
01:16:55,544 --> 01:16:57,003
Give a signal!

1246
01:17:09,763 --> 01:17:11,153
Mr. OMalley?

1247
01:17:13,516 --> 01:17:16,228
- What's up?
- A signal.

1248
01:17:18,175 --> 01:17:20,504
It's Reuter's sign.

1249
01:17:20,504 --> 01:17:22,070
- Take the package.
- Yes sir.

1250
01:18:05,215 --> 01:18:06,634
Operator!
Are you ready?

1251
01:18:06,703 --> 01:18:09,382
The lines do not
were tested.

1252
01:18:09,540 --> 01:18:11,279
Use this message as a test.

1253
01:18:13,245 --> 01:18:14,846
I'll try.

1254
01:18:15,984 --> 01:18:17,722
But I don't guarantee anything.

1255
01:18:17,722 --> 01:18:19,780
Try it, anyway.

1256
01:18:41,432 --> 01:18:42,301
Mr. Reuters.

1257
01:18:42,301 --> 01:18:43,795
Who is it now?

1258
01:18:44,665 --> 01:18:46,020
- Mr. Reuters
- Yes?

1259
01:18:47,028 --> 01:18:48,663
- It's a message from Cork!
-Cork?

1260
01:18:48,663 --> 01:18:51,013
Ida, a message from Cork!

1261
01:19:03,946 --> 01:19:05,406
What is it?

1262
01:19:12,879 --> 01:19:16,808
I would like to open the line
with other news.

1263
01:19:17,433 --> 01:19:19,207
It's terrible!

1264
01:19:19,876 --> 01:19:23,761
It should spread quickly.

1265
01:19:24,525 --> 01:19:26,959
We still caught the opening of the Stock Exchange.

1266
01:19:33,286 --> 01:19:35,129
You can't wait,

1267
01:19:35,227 --> 01:19:37,841
until Sir Randolph sells?

1268
01:19:37,841 --> 01:19:39,300
No, Ida.

1269
01:19:39,543 --> 01:19:43,263
It will be ruined.
Have you forgotten what you did for us?!

1270
01:19:43,367 --> 01:19:45,496
Of course not.

1271
01:19:45,766 --> 01:19:49,243
This belongs to the public,
not to Sir Randolph or me.

1272
01:19:50,598 --> 01:19:53,657
I can't keep this
to protect a person.

1273
01:19:58,558 --> 01:20:00,159
Get ready everyone!

1274
01:20:01,826 --> 01:20:03,739
Special newsletter!

1275
01:20:06,033 --> 01:20:08,362
Free all lines.

1276
01:20:09,717 --> 01:20:12,811
All translators!
Russian, French, Italian!

1277
01:20:12,811 --> 01:20:14,203
Quickly!

1278
01:20:19,209 --> 01:20:21,956
The Morning Herald!
Lincoln is assassinated!

1279
01:20:22,791 --> 01:20:25,675
President Lincoln,
murdered!

1280
01:20:25,675 --> 01:20:28,386
Special edition!
Lincoln is assassinated!

1281
01:20:38,398 --> 01:20:39,649
Sell!

1282
01:21:03,290 --> 01:21:06,176
The American ambassador
should know that!

1283
01:21:06,524 --> 01:21:10,834
I can only say that this news
has not been officially confirmed.

1284
01:21:11,703 --> 01:21:13,685
I don't even know where it came from,

1285
01:21:13,685 --> 01:21:16,430
the American mail boat
It hasn't arrived yet!

1286
01:21:16,569 --> 01:21:21,229
According to Anglo-Irish, the
ship has not yet been sighted.

1287
01:21:22,896 --> 01:21:27,242
Mr. Reuter will not broadcast
deliberately false rumor!

1288
01:21:27,972 --> 01:21:29,675
Sirs!

1289
01:21:35,202 --> 01:21:37,287
Rumors!
Rumors!

1290
01:21:37,490 --> 01:21:40,757
I spoke to the ambassador
American,

1291
01:21:40,757 --> 01:21:43,590
and the Company
Anglo-Irish.

1292
01:21:43,755 --> 01:21:46,779
The mail boat
hasn't been seen yet!

1293
01:21:48,516 --> 01:21:52,341
Reuters invented this
to sink the market.

1294
01:21:52,427 --> 01:21:53,767
But why?

1295
01:21:53,815 --> 01:21:56,650
You're crazy,
is almost bankrupt!

1296
01:21:56,838 --> 01:22:00,024
Without a doubt, try
earn money

1297
01:22:00,415 --> 01:22:03,902
using your reputation
of reliability.

1298
01:22:04,106 --> 01:22:05,602
Damn you!

1299
01:22:05,681 --> 01:22:08,443
- Isn't Reuter your friend?
- It was!

1300
01:22:08,539 --> 01:22:09,894
Buy!

1301
01:22:31,502 --> 01:22:33,447
They raised the flag again.

1302
01:22:35,499 --> 01:22:37,550
They don't believe me!

1303
01:22:46,944 --> 01:22:48,960
Damn you!

1304
01:22:49,132 --> 01:22:55,122
I would be ruined
if it had sold!

1305
01:22:55,326 --> 01:22:57,969
Sell ​​as quickly as possible!

1306
01:22:57,969 --> 01:22:59,324
Please,
don't waste time.

1307
01:22:59,324 --> 01:23:02,104
Don't be complicit.

1308
01:23:02,104 --> 01:23:04,607
- It's true!
- It's impossible!

1309
01:23:04,816 --> 01:23:07,318
The mail ship
hasn't been seen yet!

1310
01:23:07,423 --> 01:23:10,831
Not in Queenstowen,
but it was already in Crookshaven.

1311
01:23:10,831 --> 01:23:14,305
Max took the messages and
sent them through Cork.

1312
01:23:14,331 --> 01:23:17,113
There is no line between
Cork and Crookshaven!

1313
01:23:17,262 --> 01:23:19,278
Yes there is.

1314
01:23:19,974 --> 01:23:21,990
Thanks for your money!

1315
01:23:24,214 --> 01:23:26,440
So did the Anglo-Irish win?

1316
01:23:26,440 --> 01:23:28,004
In 7 hours!

1317
01:23:28,004 --> 01:23:30,645
Why didn't you tell me?

1318
01:23:30,645 --> 01:23:34,157
You are a member of many
clubs.

1319
01:23:34,157 --> 01:23:36,695
I could let a word slip.

1320
01:23:37,391 --> 01:23:39,197
It was a big secret!

1321
01:23:39,719 --> 01:23:42,674
Go sell your shares!

1322
01:23:42,736 --> 01:23:44,649
Immediately!
Julius!

1323
01:23:45,316 --> 01:23:47,159
I don't know what to say.

1324
01:23:47,159 --> 01:23:49,836
Don't say anything
and sell!

1325
01:23:54,981 --> 01:23:59,605
Keep the secret. I want the
Anglo-Irish confirm!

1326
01:23:59,605 --> 01:24:00,752
Accordingly!

1327
01:24:02,142 --> 01:24:04,053
See you soon!

1328
01:24:05,931 --> 01:24:07,287
He seems restless.

1329
01:24:07,287 --> 01:24:08,851
I am.

1330
01:24:10,520 --> 01:24:13,788
Your telegram will be named
in Parliament.

1331
01:24:13,788 --> 01:24:16,813
- I became a national scandal?!
- Oh, Julius!

1332
01:24:16,813 --> 01:24:18,203
Why did it?

1333
01:24:18,267 --> 01:24:20,666
Reuter is always the fastest.

1334
01:24:20,776 --> 01:24:22,619
Have you gone crazy?

1335
01:24:22,619 --> 01:24:24,807
You'll soon find out!

1336
01:24:36,141 --> 01:24:39,721
You are Reuter's friend.
Why did he spread this rumor?

1337
01:24:39,721 --> 01:24:44,102
Julius Reuter never disclosed
false rumors.

1338
01:24:44,346 --> 01:24:46,119
How will the Times react?

1339
01:24:46,119 --> 01:24:49,352
- Not yet.
- What if the news is fake?

1340
01:24:49,561 --> 01:24:52,724
So, no one will be left
at Reuters Agency for processing.

1341
01:24:59,955 --> 01:25:02,493
- I'll accompany you.
- Don't worry.

1342
01:25:03,186 --> 01:25:04,788
   Reuters!

1343
01:25:07,637 --> 01:25:10,175
How much did they pay you
to spread this rumor?

1344
01:25:10,175 --> 01:25:12,286
- What country was it?
- Millions stolen!

1345
01:25:12,713 --> 01:25:14,834
Reuter was reliable!

1346
01:25:15,181 --> 01:25:16,955
You ruined me!

1347
01:25:18,762 --> 01:25:19,910
Kill him!

1348
01:25:37,048 --> 01:25:40,385
Will the government
is willing

1349
01:25:40,385 --> 01:25:42,192
to sue this Rooter?

1350
01:25:45,843 --> 01:25:49,737
The government does not control the
country's press.

1351
01:25:51,614 --> 01:25:55,299
I propose a law to
control the press.

1352
01:25:56,516 --> 01:25:59,854
The government will oppose it.

1353
01:25:59,854 --> 01:26:04,060
Freedom of the press and freedom
of expression are inseparable.

1354
01:26:04,790 --> 01:26:09,031
And the thousands of people who
were ruined today.

1355
01:26:09,669 --> 01:26:11,304
Not to mention those...

1356
01:26:11,659 --> 01:26:14,745
that will be indirectly affected.

1357
01:26:14,976 --> 01:26:16,626
Don't these people have rights?

1358
01:26:16,915 --> 01:26:18,965
Who is responsible
of this ruin?

1359
01:26:19,529 --> 01:26:20,675
Julius Rooter!

1360
01:26:21,337 --> 01:26:23,027
A pirate!
Rooter!

1361
01:26:23,137 --> 01:26:24,549
Such a shameless man

1362
01:26:24,637 --> 01:26:28,018
who dares to sit on the press bench!

1363
01:26:28,184 --> 01:26:30,063
They make a serious mistake.

1364
01:26:30,271 --> 01:26:32,994
Mr. Reuter is your friend,
Isn't that true?

1365
01:26:33,019 --> 01:26:34,940
I'm proud to say it.

1366
01:26:35,062 --> 01:26:37,081
How much did you lose on the stock market?

1367
01:26:37,399 --> 01:26:39,066
Nothing, not a penny!

1368
01:26:39,762 --> 01:26:42,160
Are you sure the news is true?

1369
01:26:42,682 --> 01:26:44,558
I hope so!

1370
01:26:49,253 --> 01:26:51,859
Let's deliberate
this subject.

1371
01:26:54,049 --> 01:26:57,213
How can this man continue
machining,

1372
01:26:57,213 --> 01:26:59,369
protected by freedom
press?

1373
01:27:01,732 --> 01:27:04,236
The entire press

1374
01:27:04,236 --> 01:27:07,330
should not be censored
by an individual.

1375
01:27:07,330 --> 01:27:09,277
The press is
responsible for Rooter!

1376
01:27:09,589 --> 01:27:12,299
It's what makes her live!

1377
01:27:12,369 --> 01:27:15,673
The press must accept
the consequences!

1378
01:27:16,682 --> 01:27:20,053
My government
Are you willing to fight...

1379
01:27:20,053 --> 01:27:23,111
for freedom of the press.

1380
01:27:23,877 --> 01:27:26,867
But you don't have to forget

1381
01:27:26,867 --> 01:27:29,440
investor losses.

1382
01:27:33,055 --> 01:27:35,140
Gentlemen, please.

1383
01:27:35,766 --> 01:27:39,140
I just received a message
of the US ambassador.

1384
01:27:40,330 --> 01:27:43,378
Abraham Lincoln, president
in the United States,

1385
01:27:43,755 --> 01:27:46,386
was killed, murdered!

1386
01:27:53,183 --> 01:27:56,415
This tragic news
has been confirmed

1387
01:27:56,415 --> 01:27:58,920
for the company
Anglo-Irish.

1388
01:28:01,109 --> 01:28:02,361
Mr. Rooter!

1389
01:28:03,577 --> 01:28:06,915
Her Majesty's Government
offers his apologies,

1390
01:28:06,915 --> 01:28:10,462
as well as members of the
Parliament.

1391
01:28:10,532 --> 01:28:14,007
For your skill
and its veracity,

1392
01:28:14,007 --> 01:28:18,421
saved the press
of yet another attack...

1393
01:28:18,421 --> 01:28:20,579
against his freedom.

1394
01:28:21,565 --> 01:28:23,079
Thanks.

1395
01:28:24,332 --> 01:28:26,973
Gentlemen, may I speak?

1396
01:28:27,768 --> 01:28:31,732
A censored press
It is an instrument of corruption.

1397
01:28:32,016 --> 01:28:35,109
A free press symbolizes
a free people.

1398
01:28:35,734 --> 01:28:37,738
Since truth is freedom,

1399
01:28:38,169 --> 01:28:39,691
and without truth,

1400
01:28:39,942 --> 01:28:43,035
There can be no more than slavery
and degradation.

1401
01:28:46,651 --> 01:28:48,770
And gentlemen, please,

1402
01:28:49,188 --> 01:28:51,656
my name is Reuter!
